1
00:00:00,167 --> 00:00:02,317
This is already our fifth recording.

2
00:00:03,384 --> 00:00:09,210
The participants got a lot closer
while drinking and playing games.

3
00:00:09,374 --> 00:00:11,461
Are we okay staying distant like this?

4
00:00:12,346 --> 00:00:16,213
If this is where we're at after five
episodes, then we should just give up.

5
00:00:17,022 --> 00:00:19,366
- This is fine, too.
- It'll be an ambiguous ending.

6
00:00:19,391 --> 00:00:22,249
But who knows? We could
suddenly get really close.

7
00:00:22,274 --> 00:00:24,402
- That's true.
- Oh, hang on.

8
00:00:24,849 --> 00:00:26,317
Wait. There's something...

9
00:00:26,342 --> 00:00:28,389
(What's going on?)

10
00:00:29,139 --> 00:00:31,076
Oh dear!

11
00:00:31,101 --> 00:00:32,246
Oh my gosh!

12
00:00:32,271 --> 00:00:33,730
There it is!

13
00:00:37,720 --> 00:00:38,720
I knew it!

14
00:00:39,933 --> 00:00:42,374
(In the previous episode, only
Do-yeon got the right answer.)

15
00:00:42,399 --> 00:00:44,073
(She's currently in the lead!)

16
00:00:44,098 --> 00:00:46,284
I used this at Olive
Young last night.

17
00:00:47,048 --> 00:00:49,191
- Oh? You can really use it?
- Yes, I bought snacks.

18
00:00:49,462 --> 00:00:51,621
- You can buy bagel chips.
- Really?

19
00:00:52,815 --> 00:00:54,490
There's a limit of $4.50.

20
00:00:54,515 --> 00:00:57,216
I'm just kidding, but
that's how valuable this is.

21
00:00:57,241 --> 00:00:59,789
- Gosh, I'm so envious.
- You should get a coin, too.

22
00:01:00,046 --> 00:01:02,737
- I think there's a question today, too.
- There is.

23
00:01:02,762 --> 00:01:03,986
The cards are in front of us.

24
00:01:04,011 --> 00:01:06,805
Shall we check today's question first?

25
00:01:06,830 --> 00:01:08,434
I have to get it right today.

26
00:01:10,153 --> 00:01:14,734
(Today's Question: Who
will be eliminated today?)

27
00:01:15,029 --> 00:01:16,315
- Eliminated?
- Eliminated?

28
00:01:16,340 --> 00:01:18,823
Oh, there are eliminations this time, too.

29
00:01:18,848 --> 00:01:20,700
That's harsh!

30
00:01:20,725 --> 00:01:26,238
Those who are suspected to be Money
Catchers the most will be eliminated.

31
00:01:26,263 --> 00:01:28,645
- It will be decided by votes, right?
- Right.

32
00:01:28,784 --> 00:01:29,886
One man and one woman.

33
00:01:30,151 --> 00:01:32,849
Who do you think they will suspect
to be Money Catchers the most?

34
00:01:33,042 --> 00:01:38,147
Honest, Yeo-min kept
winning all the challenges,

35
00:01:38,172 --> 00:01:41,768
so I'm worried that she'll
get eliminated because many

36
00:01:41,793 --> 00:01:45,781
people will keep her in check
and see her as a Money Catcher.

37
00:01:45,806 --> 00:01:48,993
For some reason, I think Su-won is a
Money Catcher. He's so straightforward.

38
00:01:49,018 --> 00:01:52,327
From the very beginning,
he didn't take time to know

39
00:01:52,352 --> 00:01:55,910
anyone else, and he just
kept going straight for Ha-neul.

40
00:01:55,935 --> 00:01:58,073
So I think he'll be suspected.

41
00:01:58,098 --> 00:02:01,275
- Once you start suspecting...
- There's no end.

42
00:02:01,937 --> 00:02:04,469
Why is Da-Na so popular?
Is she a Money Catcher?

43
00:02:04,494 --> 00:02:07,201
- That's right!
- You all remember how it ended, right?

44
00:02:07,226 --> 00:02:08,226
The results.

45
00:02:08,251 --> 00:02:12,026
Last time, Yeo-min
won the challenge, so she was

46
00:02:12,051 --> 00:02:15,640
able to see that a majority
of the guys chose Da-Na. Right?

47
00:02:15,665 --> 00:02:17,047
- That's right.
- Yes.

48
00:02:17,072 --> 00:02:21,249
Da-Na did get a majority of the
votes, and yet, fate wasn't on her side.

49
00:02:21,274 --> 00:02:23,839
- Precisely. - She chose the only
guy who didn't choose her.

50
00:02:23,864 --> 00:02:27,738
Four men voted for her, but
she voted for someone else.

51
00:02:28,298 --> 00:02:31,926
- You remember all the details.
- Oh, you don't?

52
00:02:32,651 --> 00:02:34,887
- No, it's not that.
- Ho-jun!

53
00:02:35,388 --> 00:02:38,655
This is exactly why we're
not able to get closer!

54
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:40,902
(Reflecting)

55
00:02:41,894 --> 00:02:44,717
(Paraspara Seoul)

56
00:02:45,595 --> 00:02:48,666
(The morning of the fifth
day is particularly bright.)

57
00:02:49,206 --> 00:02:51,009
(Women's lodging)

58
00:02:52,370 --> 00:02:55,292
(Ha-neul tosses and turns
as if she's uncomfortable.)

59
00:02:56,364 --> 00:03:00,520
(She barely manages to sit
up with the heavy feelings.)

60
00:03:02,731 --> 00:03:04,778
(Flop)

61
00:03:05,513 --> 00:03:08,290
- Last night...
- She drank a lot, right?

62
00:03:09,047 --> 00:03:11,667
(Last night)

63
00:03:11,882 --> 00:03:15,216
(The coin that was always
in her locker was gone.)

64
00:03:15,241 --> 00:03:20,254
Su-won, did you have a change of heart?

65
00:03:20,807 --> 00:03:25,180
I do want to try getting to know someone.

66
00:03:26,216 --> 00:03:28,645
I'll leave it at that.

67
00:03:29,753 --> 00:03:33,808
I do understand Su-won's decision.

68
00:03:34,170 --> 00:03:35,686
He probably had the same...

69
00:03:36,963 --> 00:03:38,219
thought as me...

70
00:03:39,458 --> 00:03:43,136
(She tried to hold in her
tears, but they eventually burst.)

71
00:03:43,441 --> 00:03:44,695
She cried.

72
00:03:45,118 --> 00:03:49,896
(Last night's cruel memories
are weighing her down.)

73
00:03:56,803 --> 00:03:58,358
Her eyes are swollen!

74
00:04:00,666 --> 00:04:04,066
- Did you get some sleep, Yeo-min?
- I did, but...

75
00:04:05,954 --> 00:04:12,077
(Their own complex
feelings lead to silence.)

76
00:04:15,150 --> 00:04:18,180
- Da-Na? Da-Na?
- Hmm?

77
00:04:18,368 --> 00:04:21,154
- Is there someone you're interested in?
- Me?

78
00:04:21,179 --> 00:04:22,847
- Is there someone on your mind?
- Me?

79
00:04:23,754 --> 00:04:25,365
Me? I...

80
00:04:26,556 --> 00:04:28,024
(Concerned)

81
00:04:28,577 --> 00:04:31,694
I had a good time with
Jung-woo on the first day,

82
00:04:31,719 --> 00:04:34,960
and we went in the same
car yesterday morning, too.

83
00:04:35,417 --> 00:04:37,843
I have fun with him, and
I think we're compatible.

84
00:04:38,991 --> 00:04:40,284
Jung-woo...

85
00:04:40,682 --> 00:04:42,294
I think he's great.

86
00:04:44,012 --> 00:04:45,980
Yeo-min already knows everything.

87
00:04:47,349 --> 00:04:51,714
Won-jae was nice and fun, too.

88
00:04:52,306 --> 00:04:54,485
(Da-Na became interested in Won-jae.)

89
00:04:54,510 --> 00:04:58,826
Won-jae really doesn't act like his age.

90
00:04:59,941 --> 00:05:05,358
He addressed me as an older person,
and I wondered if I had liked younger guys.

91
00:05:05,908 --> 00:05:08,741
(Oh my goodness!)

92
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:10,594
That's how love begins.

93
00:05:11,550 --> 00:05:13,534
I wondered if I had liked younger guys.

94
00:05:16,204 --> 00:05:19,794
- That's so funny!
- I said I didn't like younger guys.

95
00:05:20,383 --> 00:05:22,964
(Yeo-min is hit with nervousness.)

96
00:05:23,100 --> 00:05:24,918
(Last night in the Room of Secrets)

97
00:05:26,525 --> 00:05:29,900
- That's right.
- Right. Yeo-min picked Won-jae.

98
00:05:31,166 --> 00:05:35,562
It was a bit complicated.
I had a lot on my mind.

99
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:41,332
For the past few days,
Won-jae and I didn't really talk.

100
00:05:41,357 --> 00:05:44,909
I wondered what was on his mind, and

101
00:05:45,583 --> 00:05:47,894
I wanted to share a deeper
conversation with him.

102
00:05:49,883 --> 00:05:52,026
- Let's go talk.
- Sure.

103
00:05:53,243 --> 00:05:55,339
(After checking who's
interested in who)

104
00:05:55,364 --> 00:05:56,364
How do you feel?

105
00:05:57,838 --> 00:06:00,203
About picking the one you're interested in?

106
00:06:01,596 --> 00:06:04,484
- What do you mean? - Did you always
like one person, or did you change?

107
00:06:05,456 --> 00:06:07,337
I'm not sure. I think it's both.

108
00:06:07,417 --> 00:06:08,694
I see.

109
00:06:09,643 --> 00:06:11,016
I think you know though.

110
00:06:11,698 --> 00:06:13,319
- Yeah, I do.
- Right?

111
00:06:13,997 --> 00:06:15,418
That's why I was bit concerned.

112
00:06:17,866 --> 00:06:19,184
You weren't concerned about me?

113
00:06:21,072 --> 00:06:24,537
Are you not interested in me anymore?

114
00:06:27,249 --> 00:06:33,815
To be honest with you, as
you saw, I kept choosing you.

115
00:06:34,647 --> 00:06:41,619
But things changed when you
chose to go on a date with Jung-woo.

116
00:06:41,905 --> 00:06:43,971
Oh, what? Me? I was gonna rest.

117
00:06:44,323 --> 00:06:45,664
(Bitter)

118
00:06:46,262 --> 00:06:50,161
So I wondered if it was
pointless to keep choosing you.

119
00:06:50,677 --> 00:06:53,504
- I thought about that a lot.
- I see.

120
00:06:55,589 --> 00:07:00,192
I thought today would be the day I
could explain to you about my choice.

121
00:07:00,792 --> 00:07:05,348
If I just focus on you from the beginning,

122
00:07:05,878 --> 00:07:11,672
the girls who like you might not be
able to approach you because of me.

123
00:07:12,170 --> 00:07:15,181
The same goes for me. The guys who
are interested in me might not be able

124
00:07:15,206 --> 00:07:16,966
to express their
feelings about me.

125
00:07:16,991 --> 00:07:19,795
That's why I decided to
hide my interest for you.

126
00:07:20,345 --> 00:07:21,869
But then I realized that...

127
00:07:23,527 --> 00:07:26,458
from your point of view, there
could be a misunderstanding.

128
00:07:27,004 --> 00:07:31,845
That's why I never gave
my coin to anyone else.

129
00:07:32,088 --> 00:07:33,088
Right.

130
00:07:33,923 --> 00:07:39,290
But when I saw that you didn't choose
me, I realized I had made a mistake.

131
00:07:41,853 --> 00:07:44,043
She must have had faith in Won-jae.

132
00:07:45,031 --> 00:07:50,713
I think Won-jae is more
interested in someone else than me.

133
00:07:52,381 --> 00:07:53,381
But...

134
00:07:54,674 --> 00:07:55,968
I had hope.

135
00:07:57,670 --> 00:08:01,569
Because the one he chose didn't choose him.

136
00:08:02,557 --> 00:08:04,168
So I'm going to think positively.

137
00:08:05,123 --> 00:08:06,431
I should get him back.

138
00:08:06,940 --> 00:08:09,006
I should do whatever
it takes to get him back.

139
00:08:10,731 --> 00:08:13,346
- She's very energetic.
- She's so cool.

140
00:08:13,371 --> 00:08:14,957
(Meanwhile, in the men's lodging...)

141
00:08:14,982 --> 00:08:16,672
- What do I do?
- What?

142
00:08:16,697 --> 00:08:19,620
Who do I choose now?
I don't think I'll be able to anymore.

143
00:08:20,798 --> 00:08:24,229
What did you two talk about last night?

144
00:08:24,405 --> 00:08:28,224
I just said, "I chose someone else because
I wanted to get to know her better."

145
00:08:28,249 --> 00:08:31,632
"It's not the final decision,"

146
00:08:32,048 --> 00:08:35,207
"so I hope you don't put
much meaning into it."

147
00:08:35,232 --> 00:08:37,704
"I didn't change my mind
because I don't like you anymore."

148
00:08:38,276 --> 00:08:39,577
That's what I told her.

149
00:08:40,717 --> 00:08:44,280
- I don't know how she'll take it.
- It must be tough for you.

150
00:08:45,205 --> 00:08:47,141
Maybe I shouldn't have picked someone else.

151
00:08:49,155 --> 00:08:52,615
(He's always been going straight, but there
are two paths of emotions before him.)

152
00:08:53,560 --> 00:08:54,912
Let's go to the dining room.

153
00:08:55,431 --> 00:08:57,129
It's too uncomfortable.
What should I do?

154
00:08:57,909 --> 00:08:59,322
- Goodness.
- It's uncomfortable.

155
00:08:59,729 --> 00:09:01,475
Isn't the blueberry weird with that?

156
00:09:02,153 --> 00:09:04,663
(Su-won quietly enters the dining room.)

157
00:09:04,688 --> 00:09:08,222
- Hello.
- Hey.

158
00:09:08,949 --> 00:09:11,735
- Hi.
- Hi, hi.

159
00:09:12,950 --> 00:09:14,641
(Looking away from him)

160
00:09:15,509 --> 00:09:18,234
(They're close but far.)

161
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:22,246
(Careful)

162
00:09:23,129 --> 00:09:27,281
(Awkwardness flows between them.)

163
00:09:29,969 --> 00:09:31,016
(Glance)

164
00:09:36,358 --> 00:09:39,303
(Su-won keeps looking at Ha-neul.)

165
00:09:41,166 --> 00:09:43,523
(Just then, Da-Na sits next to Su-won.)

166
00:09:43,548 --> 00:09:45,135
Da-Na happens to appear just then.

167
00:09:46,090 --> 00:09:47,226
(Glance)

168
00:09:49,730 --> 00:09:52,564
I can feel the awkwardness
all the way here.

169
00:09:53,567 --> 00:09:54,861
(Close)

170
00:09:57,191 --> 00:10:01,714
I think... I'm in an ambiguous spot.

171
00:10:03,054 --> 00:10:04,665
If I talk to her...

172
00:10:07,924 --> 00:10:09,265
Who is he referring to?

173
00:10:09,290 --> 00:10:12,982
(Su-won is between Ha-neul and Da-Na.)

174
00:10:13,624 --> 00:10:17,129
(Meanwhile, Ji-min is walking
around the room by herself.)

175
00:10:22,438 --> 00:10:24,654
- Why is she in here alone?
- What is she doing?

176
00:10:25,483 --> 00:10:29,549
I'm going to make up my mind and move
forward with it until the final decision.

177
00:10:29,574 --> 00:10:31,557
Wow, awesome! You?

178
00:10:31,582 --> 00:10:32,735
(Shocking confession)

179
00:10:32,760 --> 00:10:33,760
So cool!

180
00:10:34,325 --> 00:10:37,515
- You're adorable.
- She made a declaration.

181
00:10:38,091 --> 00:10:39,233
(Smile)

182
00:10:40,220 --> 00:10:41,982
Her heart must flutter thinking about it.

183
00:10:43,943 --> 00:10:46,328
(Ji-min leaves the room as if
she has made up her mind.)

184
00:10:46,666 --> 00:10:48,916
(Hop, hop)

185
00:10:51,450 --> 00:10:55,409
(She came to the men's lodging?)

186
00:10:56,532 --> 00:10:57,968
That's not the dining room.

187
00:10:59,047 --> 00:11:00,277
(Knock, knock)

188
00:11:00,920 --> 00:11:02,422
Is anyone here?

189
00:11:03,125 --> 00:11:04,839
She came to the guys' room.

190
00:11:07,717 --> 00:11:08,797
- Oh?
- Hey.

191
00:11:09,387 --> 00:11:11,799
- Are you here alone?
- They're all washing up.

192
00:11:12,037 --> 00:11:13,928
- Who's here?
- I think everyone is.

193
00:11:14,161 --> 00:11:15,573
- Everyone?
- Yeah, why?

194
00:11:16,013 --> 00:11:17,187
It's nothing.

195
00:11:18,282 --> 00:11:21,215
- Never mind. I'll come back later.
- Alright.

196
00:11:22,773 --> 00:11:25,995
- She mustered up the courage!
- She had made up her mind!

197
00:11:27,737 --> 00:11:28,921
(Lingering)

198
00:11:31,203 --> 00:11:34,194
(Ji-min came back to the room.)

199
00:11:39,475 --> 00:11:42,052
(As expected, was it too much?)

200
00:11:44,239 --> 00:11:46,430
- That's right.
- Let's go!

201
00:11:46,455 --> 00:11:47,727
(With vigor, she tries again.)

202
00:11:47,752 --> 00:11:50,274
(Will she be able to do it this time?)

203
00:11:51,320 --> 00:11:52,613
Jung-woo!

204
00:11:53,406 --> 00:11:58,219
Can you call Ji-min for me?

205
00:11:58,244 --> 00:12:00,269
- Hang on.
- Great.

206
00:12:00,294 --> 00:12:01,986
(We're proud of you, Ji-min!)

207
00:12:02,011 --> 00:12:04,378
- She really took a big step.
- She did.

208
00:12:04,595 --> 00:12:07,547
Ji-min, someone's looking for you.

209
00:12:07,987 --> 00:12:10,092
- What?
- Someone's waiting at the door for you.

210
00:12:10,541 --> 00:12:11,655
(Peek)

211
00:12:13,805 --> 00:12:16,429
(Ji-min is clueless as he comes out.)

212
00:12:18,371 --> 00:12:19,546
I'm getting all nervous.

213
00:12:19,976 --> 00:12:21,945
- Oh, Ji-min. What's up?
- Aren't you tired?

214
00:12:22,090 --> 00:12:23,391
Me? A little bit.

215
00:12:23,416 --> 00:12:24,973
- Oh, um...
- Yes?

216
00:12:25,857 --> 00:12:31,009
After we eat in the dining room and you get
some rest, do you want to hang out with me?

217
00:12:31,034 --> 00:12:32,900
(Heart attack alert!)

218
00:12:34,761 --> 00:12:37,556
- She asked him on a date!
- This is so refreshing!

219
00:12:37,893 --> 00:12:40,026
Do you want to hang out with me?

220
00:12:40,051 --> 00:12:41,823
- Hang out?
- Later in the afternoon?

221
00:12:42,809 --> 00:12:45,024
- His expression...
- Why is it in slow-motion?

222
00:12:45,049 --> 00:12:46,667
- I know.
- Answer her!

223
00:12:48,250 --> 00:12:49,450
Please say yes!

224
00:12:50,053 --> 00:12:51,388
"Let's go!"

225
00:12:52,226 --> 00:12:53,638
- Sure.
- You're up for it?

226
00:12:53,663 --> 00:12:56,131
(Time to celebrate!)

227
00:12:56,560 --> 00:12:57,751
- Sure.
- You're up for it?

228
00:12:57,776 --> 00:12:59,864
In the afternoon? Okay, you got it.

229
00:13:00,118 --> 00:13:01,118
Yay!

230
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:02,612
Sure, let's hang out.

231
00:13:02,637 --> 00:13:03,904
- Promise?
- Yeah.

232
00:13:04,460 --> 00:13:05,460
They promised!

233
00:13:05,485 --> 00:13:07,413
(They're smiling like parents.)

234
00:13:07,438 --> 00:13:09,255
What's with that pinky promise?

235
00:13:09,894 --> 00:13:11,672
- Oh my!
- My goodness!

236
00:13:11,697 --> 00:13:16,110
How exciting! She should
never wash her hands now.

237
00:13:19,141 --> 00:13:20,459
(Shy)

238
00:13:26,442 --> 00:13:27,521
(Tilt)

239
00:13:28,219 --> 00:13:29,342
What'd you guys talk about?

240
00:13:29,367 --> 00:13:34,125
I'm guessing that the girls have to
ask the guys out on a date this afternoon.

241
00:13:34,706 --> 00:13:36,525
- The girls have to ask the guys out?
- Yeah.

242
00:13:36,874 --> 00:13:38,639
- She must've asked you out.
- Yeah.

243
00:13:40,747 --> 00:13:42,985
Oh, he thinks this is a challenge!

244
00:13:43,010 --> 00:13:45,772
- Why would he think that?
- It's an unplanned date!

245
00:13:46,364 --> 00:13:50,324
But I seriously didn't think this was it.

246
00:13:52,394 --> 00:13:53,394
I'm confused.

247
00:13:55,017 --> 00:13:57,667
It's a great day today. Wanna go out?

248
00:13:59,315 --> 00:14:00,695
Wow, the weather is amazing.

249
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:02,998
(They enjoy a relaxing
breakfast on the grass.)

250
00:14:03,366 --> 00:14:06,064
All ten of us are here, right? It's great.

251
00:14:06,433 --> 00:14:09,688
(Some people are happy,
and some people aren't...)

252
00:14:09,713 --> 00:14:12,149
- Goodness.
- Oh no.

253
00:14:12,174 --> 00:14:13,811
Their expressions are dim.

254
00:14:17,761 --> 00:14:19,721
(Thinking)

255
00:14:20,287 --> 00:14:22,001
(Concerned)

256
00:14:24,650 --> 00:14:26,983
Why does Ji-min look like
he has a lot on his mind, too?

257
00:14:27,190 --> 00:14:29,525
- What's wrong?
- It's so complicated.

258
00:14:31,388 --> 00:14:33,142
- Let's go to the first floor.
- To Ha-neul?

259
00:14:33,341 --> 00:14:37,142
- The first floor? Why?
- Just.

260
00:14:41,232 --> 00:14:42,232
Sure.

261
00:14:45,233 --> 00:14:48,367
(Ji-min and Ha-neul go
spend time alone again.)

262
00:14:48,746 --> 00:14:49,945
(Uncomfortable)

263
00:14:50,694 --> 00:14:52,996
They've been talking
alone a lot since yesterday.

264
00:14:53,539 --> 00:14:55,157
I'm curious what it's about.

265
00:14:55,912 --> 00:14:57,355
I don't know what to do.

266
00:14:58,408 --> 00:15:01,473
(Because of them, there are
subtle, complex emotions.)

267
00:15:01,785 --> 00:15:03,852
Someone asked me out on a date.

268
00:15:05,091 --> 00:15:06,091
Really?

269
00:15:06,495 --> 00:15:09,187
Why are you so serious though?
Isn't it a good thing?

270
00:15:14,204 --> 00:15:17,417
Honestly, there's someone
I want to get to know.

271
00:15:18,024 --> 00:15:19,996
If I express my interest
in her but she rejects

272
00:15:20,021 --> 00:15:21,993
me, I was just gonna
be like, "Oh, well." But...

273
00:15:24,770 --> 00:15:26,445
It was someone unexpected, huh?

274
00:15:27,066 --> 00:15:31,257
I naturally thought she
didn't have any interest in me.

275
00:15:31,372 --> 00:15:33,910
So you're thinking of going
with her or the one on your mind?

276
00:15:33,935 --> 00:15:36,327
I told her yes. Of course I said yes.

277
00:15:36,630 --> 00:15:38,449
She asked me what I
was doing this afternoon.

278
00:15:38,474 --> 00:15:39,989
I mean, I don't
mind talking with her.

279
00:15:40,372 --> 00:15:42,158
- But we don't have much time.
- Right.

280
00:15:43,345 --> 00:15:45,948
- Gosh, this is hard.
- I understand where he's coming from.

281
00:15:46,650 --> 00:15:48,213
They don't have a lot of time.

282
00:15:49,439 --> 00:15:52,518
Is there anyone new
you want to get to know?

283
00:15:53,284 --> 00:15:54,967
Hmm... I'm not sure.

284
00:15:56,762 --> 00:15:59,534
(Is he asking that with her in mind?)

285
00:16:00,544 --> 00:16:02,506
We only have a few
days left, so I thought it'd

286
00:16:02,531 --> 00:16:04,411
be better for you to
cleanly move on from him.

287
00:16:04,892 --> 00:16:06,709
I don't know. It's complicated for me, too.

288
00:16:08,912 --> 00:16:11,546
You're not changing your mind.
You're not looking at other guys.

289
00:16:13,361 --> 00:16:15,655
You're really not good at
approaching people, are you?

290
00:16:15,680 --> 00:16:17,147
Yeah, I can never do that.

291
00:16:19,882 --> 00:16:22,534
Ha-neul has a hard time expressing herself.

292
00:16:22,559 --> 00:16:25,936
For some reason, I think
Ji-min has feelings for Ha-neul.

293
00:16:25,961 --> 00:16:28,228
- I'm getting that, too.
- Right?

294
00:16:28,253 --> 00:16:30,933
My heart fluttered in that scene.

295
00:16:31,228 --> 00:16:34,355
- Right now?
- When Ji-min was talking to Ha-neul.

296
00:16:34,717 --> 00:16:36,384
- From a woman's POV?
- My heart.

297
00:16:36,576 --> 00:16:40,496
- When he said what?
- Everything.

298
00:16:40,521 --> 00:16:42,944
Right. It's kind of thrilling, isn't it?

299
00:16:43,878 --> 00:16:46,877
- With a small opportunity, they
can get connected. - Exactly.

300
00:16:46,902 --> 00:16:48,342
I think he likes her.

301
00:16:48,367 --> 00:16:50,826
Why is he asking Ha-neul for advice?

302
00:16:54,641 --> 00:16:57,031
- Oh! What's that sound?
- What's happening?

303
00:16:57,352 --> 00:16:58,352
Girls!

304
00:16:58,743 --> 00:17:01,441
- What's that?
- Something showed up.

305
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:03,419
What is it? A challenge?

306
00:17:05,416 --> 00:17:06,416
Oh my god.

307
00:17:06,441 --> 00:17:08,417
(Today, the men will prepare
dates. The women who

308
00:17:08,442 --> 00:17:10,378
receive an invitation
should go to the location.)

309
00:17:10,403 --> 00:17:12,762
Someone might not get an invitation.

310
00:17:13,430 --> 00:17:15,710
- Why am I suddenly
getting sad? - No way.

311
00:17:15,735 --> 00:17:18,847
If you get more than one invitation,
do you go on different dates?

312
00:17:18,977 --> 00:17:22,103
No. You should only receive one invitation.

313
00:17:22,696 --> 00:17:23,886
It's so uncomfortable.

314
00:17:24,635 --> 00:17:26,579
Oh, so this is how it's going to be.

315
00:17:28,210 --> 00:17:31,384
Gosh, this is driving me nuts! Wow!

316
00:17:31,409 --> 00:17:33,958
(The guys are just as confused.)

317
00:17:35,447 --> 00:17:37,883
- We have to write the invitation.
- Write it?

318
00:17:40,079 --> 00:17:41,968
They have to write it themselves?

319
00:17:43,278 --> 00:17:46,574
(Who will they ask out on a date?)

320
00:17:48,087 --> 00:17:49,769
Something appeared.
Something popped up.

321
00:17:50,166 --> 00:17:52,517
- Something popped up.
- Hurry, hurry, hurry!

322
00:17:53,260 --> 00:17:58,690
(Personally invite her to your space.)

323
00:17:58,715 --> 00:18:01,309
(Write down your name, the
location of the date, etc. and

324
00:18:01,334 --> 00:18:04,062
personally give it to the one
you want to go on a date with.)

325
00:18:04,087 --> 00:18:07,152
Does that mean we have to knock
on the door and give it to them?

326
00:18:07,478 --> 00:18:10,624
- Can't you give it secretly?
- Sure, it's up to you.

327
00:18:11,628 --> 00:18:12,787
This will be interesting.

328
00:18:13,163 --> 00:18:17,894
- Jung-woo is the only one at peace here.
- "This will be interesting."

329
00:18:19,001 --> 00:18:20,835
I think Su-won has the
biggest dilemma here.

330
00:18:20,860 --> 00:18:22,249
Right, that's true.

331
00:18:22,379 --> 00:18:27,420
If I choose her as usual, then what was
the point of the decision I made yesterday?

332
00:18:28,019 --> 00:18:30,801
On the other hand, if I
go with my decision from

333
00:18:30,826 --> 00:18:34,029
yesterday, I'll feel really
guilty to the first girl...

334
00:18:35,631 --> 00:18:37,567
So I have no idea what I should do.

335
00:18:38,141 --> 00:18:39,879
It must be really tough for him.

336
00:18:40,874 --> 00:18:42,414
I think he fell into a trap.

337
00:18:42,677 --> 00:18:44,733
No matter what he
chooses, it'll be difficult.

338
00:18:44,758 --> 00:18:46,608
But didn't everyone here fall into a trap?

339
00:18:48,866 --> 00:18:49,866
It's hard.

340
00:18:52,402 --> 00:18:56,791
(The men are caught in invisible traps.)

341
00:18:58,011 --> 00:19:01,712
I'm so curious about Jung-woo.
I wonder who he'll choose.

342
00:19:01,737 --> 00:19:05,039
- Oh. - He seems to have
made up his mind yesterday.

343
00:19:05,064 --> 00:19:06,321
Really?

344
00:19:06,750 --> 00:19:08,241
I don't know about the others.

345
00:19:09,397 --> 00:19:13,571
I don't know about any
of them. All five of them.

346
00:19:15,013 --> 00:19:17,362
I don't think anyone here feels at ease.

347
00:19:19,208 --> 00:19:21,326
(The men will give an
invitation with the location

348
00:19:21,351 --> 00:19:23,338
of the date to the woman
they want to invite.)

349
00:19:23,363 --> 00:19:26,841
(The woman may reject his invitation.)

350
00:19:29,650 --> 00:19:33,365
(They write each letter with sincerity.)

351
00:19:35,568 --> 00:19:37,925
(Meanwhile...)

352
00:19:38,524 --> 00:19:39,952
It's Ji-min and Su-won.

353
00:19:39,977 --> 00:19:43,420
(Su-won and Ji-min are thinking
deeply about the invitation.)

354
00:19:47,698 --> 00:19:52,279
(Why are they
thinking so deeply...?)

355
00:19:56,549 --> 00:20:00,326
(Su-won starts to
write his invitation first.)

356
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:04,627
(Thinking)

357
00:20:06,448 --> 00:20:08,638
Oh no, he's having such a hard time.

358
00:20:09,440 --> 00:20:12,292
(Who will receive Su-won's invitation?)

359
00:20:12,869 --> 00:20:14,326
(See you later...)

360
00:20:17,543 --> 00:20:18,885
Did you make a decision?

361
00:20:18,910 --> 00:20:21,334
I wrote it. I don't
know. I just wrote it.

362
00:20:21,971 --> 00:20:23,733
I haven't decided yet.

363
00:20:24,266 --> 00:20:27,316
(Unlike before, Su-won
had to especially think a lot.)

364
00:20:28,689 --> 00:20:32,257
(After writing down his feelings with a
lot of thought, whom will he give this to?)

365
00:20:33,335 --> 00:20:36,336
(After much thought, they delivered
the invitation with their sincerity.)

366
00:20:37,260 --> 00:20:39,611
("The Men's Invitation"
will unfold away from

367
00:20:39,636 --> 00:20:41,832
the Love mansion
and in the city of Seoul.)

368
00:20:43,154 --> 00:20:46,415
There are many amazing
dating spots in Seoul.

369
00:20:47,798 --> 00:20:50,437
(In the places where
they invited the women...)

370
00:20:50,832 --> 00:20:53,836
(they will have the time to approach
the women in the most sincere way.)

371
00:20:55,094 --> 00:20:56,094
Hang on.

372
00:20:56,119 --> 00:20:58,969
Wasn't there a photo of
Jae-hyung on that building?

373
00:20:59,813 --> 00:21:01,148
- What the heck?
- Seriously?

374
00:21:01,173 --> 00:21:02,410
- Really?
- Is that Jae-hyung?

375
00:21:02,435 --> 00:21:06,158
- The cars, too...
- Those parked cars.

376
00:21:08,399 --> 00:21:11,613
(The men prepared dates...)

377
00:21:12,245 --> 00:21:14,497
(to show her their true
selves to the women.)

378
00:21:14,522 --> 00:21:18,153
That's right. They'll choose a place
where they can show off their charms.

379
00:21:19,196 --> 00:21:20,775
I bet they'll be nervous.

380
00:21:23,789 --> 00:21:28,606
We first had a party at a bar, and
that's where we met for the first time.

381
00:21:29,311 --> 00:21:31,953
- I talked with her a lot then.
- I see.

382
00:21:31,978 --> 00:21:34,838
I spoke with her a lot, and I thought she

383
00:21:34,863 --> 00:21:37,592
was nice, so I wanted
to talk with her more.

384
00:21:37,617 --> 00:21:38,617
I see.

385
00:21:38,642 --> 00:21:40,835
So his friend is joining them.

386
00:21:41,163 --> 00:21:42,894
I don't know if I'll be able to eat.

387
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:46,476
I'm more nervous than you.

388
00:21:46,972 --> 00:21:48,662
I met Young-Jin at a cram school.

389
00:21:48,687 --> 00:21:51,649
We've known each other
for about ten years now.

390
00:21:52,327 --> 00:21:54,968
Sometimes, we talk to each
other on the phone at night

391
00:21:54,993 --> 00:21:57,345
and talk to each other
about the smallest things.

392
00:21:58,213 --> 00:22:01,426
The date spot is a delicious
pasta restaurant where I

393
00:22:01,451 --> 00:22:04,960
spent time with meaningful
people ever since I was younger.

394
00:22:06,650 --> 00:22:09,421
(The silhouette of a long-haired
woman who is coming to see Ji-min)

395
00:22:09,446 --> 00:22:10,939
(Who is she?)

396
00:22:10,964 --> 00:22:13,766
Didn't it seem like Ha-neul because
of the way her hair looked?

397
00:22:13,974 --> 00:22:16,048
- I thought it was Ji-min.
- Isn't it Ji-min?

398
00:22:16,905 --> 00:22:20,264
(Step by step, she's getting closer.)

399
00:22:20,673 --> 00:22:22,197
What? Is it Ji-min?

400
00:22:23,843 --> 00:22:24,843
Who is it?

401
00:22:26,458 --> 00:22:27,545
You're here.

402
00:22:28,269 --> 00:22:31,531
- Who is it?
- Wait a minute. He looks thrilled.

403
00:22:31,732 --> 00:22:33,668
- I'm nervous.
- I think it's Ji-min.

404
00:22:33,693 --> 00:22:36,171
(The one Ahn Ji-min
invited is Yang Ji-min.)

405
00:22:36,729 --> 00:22:38,634
- It's Ji-min!
- Ji-min!

406
00:22:38,659 --> 00:22:39,946
What's going on?

407
00:22:40,361 --> 00:22:41,361
You're here.

408
00:22:41,568 --> 00:22:43,163
- Oh, hello.
- Hello.

409
00:22:43,974 --> 00:22:44,974
Sit here.

410
00:22:46,118 --> 00:22:48,025
- Is he your friend?
- Yeah.

411
00:22:48,050 --> 00:22:49,266
Hello.

412
00:22:49,291 --> 00:22:51,283
- This is awesome.
- He made the right choice.

413
00:22:52,016 --> 00:22:55,486
First off, I was grateful for
her courage this morning.

414
00:22:55,990 --> 00:22:58,505
- Do you want to hang out
with me today? - Hang out?

415
00:22:58,530 --> 00:22:59,730
Later in the afternoon?

416
00:23:00,344 --> 00:23:01,744
- Sure.
- It's okay?

417
00:23:01,769 --> 00:23:04,528
And I was worried that I would hurt her.

418
00:23:05,122 --> 00:23:07,719
For those reasons, I eventually chose her.

419
00:23:08,128 --> 00:23:10,105
- I see.
- He made a great choice.

420
00:23:10,130 --> 00:23:11,886
Ji-min, can you come here for a sec?

421
00:23:13,794 --> 00:23:15,571
Go out with me.

422
00:23:16,813 --> 00:23:18,868
My courage worked.

423
00:23:19,347 --> 00:23:21,189
Yay! That's what I thought.

424
00:23:21,777 --> 00:23:23,604
(Are you a robot?)

425
00:23:23,668 --> 00:23:25,097
She's happy right?

426
00:23:26,695 --> 00:23:28,044
Why is she so adorable?

427
00:23:29,812 --> 00:23:32,891
Ji-min and I didn't really talk much.

428
00:23:33,243 --> 00:23:36,013
Isn't there a time where
everyone can talk separately?

429
00:23:36,651 --> 00:23:40,659
You can muster up the
courage and ask to talk to them.

430
00:23:41,752 --> 00:23:45,897
But we do have bit of an age gap.

431
00:23:46,423 --> 00:23:48,812
Honestly, I was concerned about that.

432
00:23:50,166 --> 00:23:55,119
As you can tell, he's not the
type to make up stuff or tell lies.

433
00:23:55,648 --> 00:23:59,512
He doesn't even try to. He gets
really stressed out about lying.

434
00:23:59,537 --> 00:24:04,302
He was stressing out today, too.
He was grabbing onto his hair.

435
00:24:04,327 --> 00:24:06,236
You've got it all wrong.
I wasn't stressed out.

436
00:24:06,261 --> 00:24:10,658
I saw everything. Did you know that
the women's powder room has a window?

437
00:24:10,683 --> 00:24:11,683
(Flustered)

438
00:24:11,708 --> 00:24:14,442
- You can see me?
- We were all watching you.

439
00:24:14,467 --> 00:24:16,707
(You saw me...?)

440
00:24:17,011 --> 00:24:18,662
What's Ji-min doing over there?

441
00:24:19,565 --> 00:24:22,172
(They're all watching him.)

442
00:24:23,230 --> 00:24:27,454
(Ji-min had been watching him stress out.)

443
00:24:28,315 --> 00:24:30,292
(Embarrassed)

444
00:24:31,050 --> 00:24:32,584
You really had no idea?

445
00:24:33,287 --> 00:24:35,671
- Did you see everything
that happened today? - Yes.

446
00:24:35,696 --> 00:24:37,680
- "What is he doing?"
- We all saw it.

447
00:24:38,755 --> 00:24:39,922
I wanna go home.

448
00:24:41,287 --> 00:24:43,543
(LOL)

449
00:24:44,127 --> 00:24:47,008
(A pasta of memories he wants
to share with a special person)

450
00:24:47,135 --> 00:24:49,494
Should we eat? Try it. It's really good.

451
00:24:54,589 --> 00:24:55,970
(How is it?)

452
00:24:58,294 --> 00:24:59,444
- Is it good?
- Yes.

453
00:24:59,469 --> 00:25:00,604
- It's yummy, huh?
- Yes.

454
00:25:00,858 --> 00:25:03,065
The pollack roe is totally delicious, too.

455
00:25:03,469 --> 00:25:04,663
(I'm glad.)

456
00:25:07,884 --> 00:25:10,431
You know in the interview
we did before the show?

457
00:25:10,456 --> 00:25:13,998
What did you say when they asked you about
the youngest age you're comfortable dating?

458
00:25:14,023 --> 00:25:16,294
- Did they ask me that? I
don't remember. - Really?

459
00:25:16,495 --> 00:25:20,266
During the interview, I answered
the question about the age gap.

460
00:25:20,577 --> 00:25:23,961
They asked me if it'd be okay if
someone the age of 30 is on the show.

461
00:25:24,488 --> 00:25:30,075
I said that I feel an age
gap with people in their 30s

462
00:25:30,629 --> 00:25:32,184
and that it'd be a bit burdensome.

463
00:25:32,209 --> 00:25:33,557
I don't think you
can eat anymore.

464
00:25:33,582 --> 00:25:36,032
That's what I said, but I
saw the way Ji-min acted,

465
00:25:36,057 --> 00:25:39,675
and despite his age, I liked him.

466
00:25:41,253 --> 00:25:44,005
(She said... she likes him...)

467
00:25:44,406 --> 00:25:47,334
- How is it? Is your heart racing?
- Yes!

468
00:25:47,861 --> 00:25:53,206
Despite his age, I liked him.

469
00:25:53,914 --> 00:25:56,971
We were able to have this date
because I mustered up the courage.

470
00:25:56,996 --> 00:25:58,217
- Really?
- Yes.

471
00:25:58,242 --> 00:25:59,242
That's not true.

472
00:25:59,267 --> 00:26:00,792
Didn't he ask you out?

473
00:26:00,817 --> 00:26:02,843
He made the final decision.

474
00:26:05,809 --> 00:26:08,015
But I seriously wanted to talk with you.

475
00:26:08,040 --> 00:26:09,507
- You mean it?
- Yes.

476
00:26:10,391 --> 00:26:13,631
- My goodness.
- She's cute. Why is she so cute?

477
00:26:14,239 --> 00:26:15,795
But I didn't know.

478
00:26:15,820 --> 00:26:20,050
You know how we have to express our
interest in that room with the coins?

479
00:26:20,785 --> 00:26:28,055
But with that, I couldn't guess if you
were going to ask me out on a date.

480
00:26:28,842 --> 00:26:32,976
But I kept talking about
you from the beginning.

481
00:26:34,902 --> 00:26:38,490
- Wow, she's really honest though.
- She's just spilling everything.

482
00:26:38,931 --> 00:26:41,405
I picked you when asked
about the coins and when

483
00:26:41,583 --> 00:26:44,132
someone asked me about the
most favorable first impression.

484
00:26:44,157 --> 00:26:46,278
But I was No. 2. Someone else was No. 1.

485
00:26:46,303 --> 00:26:51,197
That's not it. I was asked
about that, and you were there.

486
00:26:51,222 --> 00:26:53,754
I wanted to express my interest in you,

487
00:26:53,955 --> 00:26:56,264
so I said it was you.

488
00:26:56,558 --> 00:26:58,337
It wasn't about first or second.

489
00:26:58,362 --> 00:26:59,538
I thought it was.

490
00:27:02,219 --> 00:27:03,619
I feel like an idiot.

491
00:27:04,251 --> 00:27:05,537
He really must not have known.

492
00:27:05,562 --> 00:27:08,922
The truth is, there was a misunderstanding.
Even about that question, too.

493
00:27:09,655 --> 00:27:14,580
I thought you never chose me in
the Room of Expressing Interests.

494
00:27:14,605 --> 00:27:15,850
- I see.
- Yeah.

495
00:27:15,875 --> 00:27:20,121
Honestly, does second place
even mean anything important?

496
00:27:21,215 --> 00:27:22,548
That's what I thought.

497
00:27:24,337 --> 00:27:29,328
Whenever I opened Ji-min's
locker, only my coin was in there.

498
00:27:29,783 --> 00:27:32,478
(From the beginning, she had
been expressing her interest in him.)

499
00:27:32,503 --> 00:27:35,814
But he thought he was someone else.

500
00:27:36,176 --> 00:27:39,960
That makes me upset and frustrated.

501
00:27:41,163 --> 00:27:42,763
Who did he think it was?

502
00:27:43,077 --> 00:27:46,738
- That's why you have to talk.
- I love this date.

503
00:27:47,942 --> 00:27:49,425
I'm going to use the restroom.

504
00:27:50,769 --> 00:27:52,301
Do you have any
questions about Ji-min?

505
00:27:52,326 --> 00:27:54,898
It seems like he's not sure
about his feelings, right?

506
00:27:55,306 --> 00:27:58,981
He always has a lot of trivial thoughts.

507
00:27:59,883 --> 00:28:01,295
Is it because of our age gap?

508
00:28:01,320 --> 00:28:05,868
I'd be lying if I said that
wasn't one of the reasons.

509
00:28:07,033 --> 00:28:09,593
He's really stressed
out, so he keeps talking

510
00:28:09,618 --> 00:28:12,066
privately with one of
the girls on the show.

511
00:28:12,261 --> 00:28:15,808
So I thought, "They're really busy."

512
00:28:16,169 --> 00:28:21,218
And on top of that, he could be into her.

513
00:28:21,587 --> 00:28:23,381
They might not be
talking about his problems.

514
00:28:23,406 --> 00:28:25,025
We don't know what
they're discussing.

515
00:28:25,050 --> 00:28:26,241
That's what I thought.

516
00:28:26,868 --> 00:28:31,101
When we play the Truth Game,
he asks another girl a lot of questions.

517
00:28:31,297 --> 00:28:32,297
Really?

518
00:28:33,804 --> 00:28:36,736
(Will they be able to resolve
the misunderstandings?)

519
00:28:37,372 --> 00:28:38,627
(Meanwhile...)

520
00:28:41,197 --> 00:28:42,569
- A cafe?
- A cafe?

521
00:28:42,594 --> 00:28:44,277
(One man is waiting for his date.)

522
00:28:46,396 --> 00:28:47,396
It's Su-won.

523
00:28:49,905 --> 00:28:55,455
I worked here for a long time when
I was in my early 20s and in college.

524
00:28:55,665 --> 00:29:00,086
And I think if we talk in a
pleasant environment like this,

525
00:29:00,111 --> 00:29:03,248
we'll be able to know each
other more comfortably.

526
00:29:03,346 --> 00:29:06,213
That's why I chose to
have the date at a cafe.

527
00:29:06,769 --> 00:29:09,969
(Who did he invite to the cafe that
is filled with his college memories?)

528
00:29:10,161 --> 00:29:12,401
(Is it Ha-neul, the one he
straightforwardly went after?)

529
00:29:12,426 --> 00:29:15,894
(Or is it Da-Na, the one
he wants to get to know?)

530
00:29:16,280 --> 00:29:18,709
(He waits for her
with a nervous heart...)

531
00:29:19,196 --> 00:29:21,141
- Welcome.
- Hello.

532
00:29:22,101 --> 00:29:23,101
Hi.

533
00:29:23,302 --> 00:29:24,611
Hello.

534
00:29:24,636 --> 00:29:28,423
(After much thought, he
gave Da-Na the invitation.)

535
00:29:28,464 --> 00:29:29,864
Hello.

536
00:29:29,976 --> 00:29:32,033
After thinking, he
eventually chose Da-Na.

537
00:29:33,019 --> 00:29:35,455
- This is for you.
- Me? Me?

538
00:29:35,789 --> 00:29:37,323
- Yeah.
- Really?

539
00:29:37,348 --> 00:29:39,206
Yeah. Read it.

540
00:29:40,199 --> 00:29:42,981
(After pondering, he gave
the invitation to Da-Na.)

541
00:29:45,032 --> 00:29:47,015
Oh no.

542
00:29:47,423 --> 00:29:49,741
Ha-neul shared her problems
with Da-Na the other day.

543
00:29:50,204 --> 00:29:51,276
Hello.

544
00:29:51,998 --> 00:29:53,261
Do you want something to drink?

545
00:29:53,286 --> 00:29:54,553
Something to drink?

546
00:29:54,909 --> 00:29:56,440
Something you're good at making?

547
00:29:56,727 --> 00:30:00,810
- I can prepare a latte for you.
- Sure, sounds good.

548
00:30:00,835 --> 00:30:02,548
- Something warm?
- Yes, that's good.

549
00:30:02,573 --> 00:30:04,003
Do you want to come in?

550
00:30:06,909 --> 00:30:09,391
You know how to make coffee?

551
00:30:09,598 --> 00:30:12,059
I've never seen you make it
at the Love Mansion before.

552
00:30:12,084 --> 00:30:15,355
- I only know the basics.
- I see.

553
00:30:15,914 --> 00:30:16,914
(Lean)

554
00:30:16,939 --> 00:30:18,669
(They get closer bit by bit.)

555
00:30:18,694 --> 00:30:20,259
(Skillful)

556
00:30:20,847 --> 00:30:22,174
You're pretty good.

557
00:30:23,852 --> 00:30:25,526
(Sincere)

558
00:30:26,478 --> 00:30:29,197
I knew how to make a heart,

559
00:30:30,628 --> 00:30:32,056
but I don't know if it'll work.

560
00:30:33,957 --> 00:30:35,552
It just has to taste good.

561
00:30:36,742 --> 00:30:38,406
But the steam looks pretty.

562
00:30:39,446 --> 00:30:43,131
Yeah, but I can't seem to do this well.

563
00:30:44,293 --> 00:30:47,801
The syrup is going all over the
place. How nervous must he be?

564
00:30:48,148 --> 00:30:51,045
I think it might leave the cup.

565
00:30:51,937 --> 00:30:53,135
Ah, I messed up.

566
00:30:53,691 --> 00:30:55,088
That's so cute.

567
00:30:55,719 --> 00:30:57,988
- Let's go to the third floor.
- The third floor?

568
00:31:01,374 --> 00:31:04,645
(Su-won and Da-Na start their date.)

569
00:31:06,436 --> 00:31:07,547
(Stare)

570
00:31:07,572 --> 00:31:10,708
Open it. It's hot, so be careful.

571
00:31:13,403 --> 00:31:16,000
I think it's gone. I think it disappeared.

572
00:31:16,025 --> 00:31:17,708
(Embarrassed/Regretful)

573
00:31:17,733 --> 00:31:19,988
He looks really nervous.

574
00:31:20,013 --> 00:31:21,943
He's different from when
he was with Ha-neul.

575
00:31:22,534 --> 00:31:24,708
- It doesn't look pretty.
- No, it's good.

576
00:31:24,733 --> 00:31:26,812
- That's unfortunate.
- It's good.

577
00:31:27,205 --> 00:31:29,605
- Make it for me again next time.
- Okay.

578
00:31:31,003 --> 00:31:35,240
What did you think? Did you
know I would choose you or not?

579
00:31:36,787 --> 00:31:39,763
- I actually didn't expect it at all?
- You didn't?

580
00:31:40,958 --> 00:31:47,951
When you gave me the invitation,
I thought, "Me? Is it really me?"

581
00:31:48,601 --> 00:31:54,410
Since you checked your locker
yesterday, didn't you kind of expect this?

582
00:31:56,131 --> 00:31:57,598
She had so many coins.

583
00:31:57,741 --> 00:32:00,466
(Room of Expressing Interests)

584
00:32:02,881 --> 00:32:06,258
(The coin that was
always in Ha-neul's locker...)

585
00:32:06,870 --> 00:32:10,358
(was moved to Da-na's
locker for the first time.)

586
00:32:12,496 --> 00:32:14,006
(Shaking pupils)

587
00:32:15,208 --> 00:32:17,104
- I wonder how she felt then.
- Me, too.

588
00:32:17,560 --> 00:32:19,854
Didn't you kind of expect this?

589
00:32:21,651 --> 00:32:24,833
I thought it was a little bit possible.

590
00:32:24,858 --> 00:32:29,943
- We've never talked before.
- We've barely talked.

591
00:32:29,968 --> 00:32:34,264
So I thought it's possible that
you chose me because of that.

592
00:32:35,421 --> 00:32:39,309
We didn't have many
chances to talk to each other.

593
00:32:40,075 --> 00:32:42,186
Starting from the second day to now.

594
00:32:43,159 --> 00:32:46,992
I wanted to talk with you,
so that's why I chose you.

595
00:32:48,292 --> 00:32:51,004
(Da-na's expression
is full of mixed feelings.)

596
00:32:51,029 --> 00:32:53,102
(Nervous)

597
00:32:53,503 --> 00:32:56,050
Anyhow, thanks for choosing me.

598
00:32:56,688 --> 00:32:58,021
- Sure.
- "Anyhow"?

599
00:32:59,382 --> 00:33:01,008
She's not really comfortable.

600
00:33:03,569 --> 00:33:05,966
- How tall are you?
- 170 centimeters.

601
00:33:07,706 --> 00:33:08,706
You're tall.

602
00:33:09,815 --> 00:33:12,217
(Su-won mentioned tall
girls are his ideal type.)

603
00:33:12,324 --> 00:33:15,554
Where do you usually
spend time the most in Seoul?

604
00:33:15,954 --> 00:33:18,193
- I don't leave Gangnam.
- Really?

605
00:33:18,218 --> 00:33:20,131
- Yeah.
- I guess you don't go far.

606
00:33:20,758 --> 00:33:23,046
(He lives in Changwon, and
she doesn't go to far places.)

607
00:33:23,071 --> 00:33:24,628
I'm a real homebody.

608
00:33:25,997 --> 00:33:28,862
- You probably cook your meals then.
- Yeah, I do.

609
00:33:28,887 --> 00:33:32,550
Do you know how to cook?
Is that why you did it on the first day?

610
00:33:32,575 --> 00:33:33,820
Well, just a bit.

611
00:33:35,569 --> 00:33:36,601
It's awkward.

612
00:33:37,056 --> 00:33:40,693
Their conversation isn't flowing.
It abruptly stops from time to time.

613
00:33:42,650 --> 00:33:45,451
You don't have any questions about me?

614
00:33:45,476 --> 00:33:48,326
Questions? Questions...

615
00:33:49,116 --> 00:33:50,981
(Anticipating)

616
00:33:52,116 --> 00:33:54,151
How's life at the Love Mansion these days?

617
00:33:55,948 --> 00:34:01,136
It's emotionally heavy to a certain extent.

618
00:34:01,161 --> 00:34:03,764
I'm losing weight... I think I'm
losing weight as time goes on.

619
00:34:05,858 --> 00:34:12,307
Ha-neul and Su-won kind of give
off "official couple" vibes, you know?

620
00:34:12,332 --> 00:34:14,507
Right. That's tough.

621
00:34:14,532 --> 00:34:17,811
(Last night, after checking the lockers,
Ha-neul shared her problems with Da-Na.)

622
00:34:17,836 --> 00:34:19,303
I didn’t get any coins today.

623
00:34:20,536 --> 00:34:22,172
- Really?
- Yeah, there are none.

624
00:34:22,989 --> 00:34:26,279
(Da-Na sincerely listens
to what Ha-neul has to say.)

625
00:34:26,726 --> 00:34:29,126
I feel like I'm the only fool.

626
00:34:31,130 --> 00:34:34,908
She told me he chose someone else.

627
00:34:36,167 --> 00:34:37,642
I felt so bad.

628
00:34:38,134 --> 00:34:39,134
Right.

629
00:34:39,678 --> 00:34:43,440
So I felt uncomfortable.

630
00:34:45,302 --> 00:34:46,302
It's awkward.

631
00:34:49,150 --> 00:34:53,078
- I definitely understand what's going on.
- He must be in a tough spot.

632
00:34:53,103 --> 00:34:54,747
He chose her after much thought.

633
00:34:55,947 --> 00:35:00,163
(Ha-neul and Yeo-min didn't
get asked out on a date.)

634
00:35:01,040 --> 00:35:02,786
- Amazing!
- It's really wonderful.

635
00:35:03,474 --> 00:35:06,124
- I can breathe freely.
- Yes.

636
00:35:11,404 --> 00:35:14,094
Why do those words
"do not lean" feel so cold?

637
00:35:14,119 --> 00:35:17,154
- It's lonely.
- "You must deal with it on your own."

638
00:35:17,179 --> 00:35:18,685
"Do not lean on anyone."

639
00:35:20,539 --> 00:35:22,198
What do you think they're doing?

640
00:35:22,223 --> 00:35:23,490
I'm really curious.

641
00:35:23,844 --> 00:35:25,939
- Let's boast about this to them later.
- Okay.

642
00:35:25,964 --> 00:35:27,139
"We went to the rooftop."

643
00:35:27,450 --> 00:35:30,784
"There was a pool and the Bukhansan."

644
00:35:31,400 --> 00:35:33,248
But they went on dates.

645
00:35:33,887 --> 00:35:35,466
But there were no men.

646
00:35:37,294 --> 00:35:38,906
It's so sad.

647
00:35:39,551 --> 00:35:40,551
It's so nice.

648
00:35:43,716 --> 00:35:46,094
(Soon, the sun goes down...)

649
00:35:47,223 --> 00:35:51,074
(Night has fallen over Seoul.)

650
00:35:51,826 --> 00:35:54,525
(There are shadows on
Yeo-min's and Ha-neul's faces, too.)

651
00:35:55,691 --> 00:35:58,720
(The day full of waiting
feels longer than ever...)

652
00:35:59,445 --> 00:36:01,287
If I'm solo this year,
too, that would mean I

653
00:36:01,874 --> 00:36:03,694
haven't been in a
relationship for five years.

654
00:36:05,054 --> 00:36:08,642
It's my fifth winter without a boyfriend.

655
00:36:09,201 --> 00:36:10,801
My fifth solo Christmas.

656
00:36:11,275 --> 00:36:17,465
Honestly, I haven't been
in many relationships,

657
00:36:17,799 --> 00:36:21,560
but in my early 20s, I dated a lot...

658
00:36:21,859 --> 00:36:24,580
Actually, rather than dates,
they were more like experiences.

659
00:36:24,893 --> 00:36:28,083
There was someone I really liked, too.

660
00:36:28,108 --> 00:36:29,108
Same here.

661
00:36:29,468 --> 00:36:31,111
I had a lot of experiences, too.

662
00:36:31,382 --> 00:36:33,914
Which makes me more careful.

663
00:36:35,769 --> 00:36:38,325
- Right. - Even if I try to date,
I just can't do it.

664
00:36:38,637 --> 00:36:40,438
Because I don't want to get hurt again.

665
00:36:42,039 --> 00:36:44,070
I experienced many heartbreaks.

666
00:36:45,558 --> 00:36:50,716
I was too nice to my first boyfriend,

667
00:36:51,691 --> 00:36:54,111
so he spoke very harshly to me.

668
00:36:54,560 --> 00:36:58,790
"I don't want you, but it's
a pity to throw you away."

669
00:36:59,563 --> 00:37:01,163
He even said that to me.

670
00:37:01,463 --> 00:37:03,931
My second boyfriend just
bluntly said he was sick of me.

671
00:37:04,856 --> 00:37:09,253
My third boyfriend said his
feelings for me were disappearing,

672
00:37:09,714 --> 00:37:11,867
but I was always the same.

673
00:37:11,892 --> 00:37:15,029
So he was burdened by me.

674
00:37:16,273 --> 00:37:20,217
I really liked them, but
we broke up like that.

675
00:37:20,905 --> 00:37:24,349
For me, I just liked them.

676
00:37:24,543 --> 00:37:28,123
They were my boyfriends, so I
made an effort to keep liking them.

677
00:37:28,978 --> 00:37:32,160
I constantly wondered if it was my fault.

678
00:37:32,185 --> 00:37:34,027
I started blaming myself.

679
00:37:34,052 --> 00:37:36,625
(Due to repeated heartbreaks,
Yeo-min blamed herself.)

680
00:37:37,169 --> 00:37:39,238
I got really hurt in my
previous relationship.

681
00:37:40,235 --> 00:37:43,412
So I keep reminding myself
that, no matter who I meet,

682
00:37:44,021 --> 00:37:47,589
I won't be like that again
and give them my everything.

683
00:37:49,173 --> 00:37:51,348
I think it was my first love.

684
00:37:51,762 --> 00:37:53,231
It was my first love,

685
00:37:54,374 --> 00:37:57,512
and I liked him a lot,
but I was really hurt.

686
00:37:58,286 --> 00:38:01,159
So after him, I thought I
won't be able to date again.

687
00:38:02,064 --> 00:38:06,013
I thought he was bright and lively,

688
00:38:06,515 --> 00:38:09,326
but he'd get violent when he drank,

689
00:38:10,772 --> 00:38:13,438
and he was really jealous and obsessive.

690
00:38:13,975 --> 00:38:18,081
After we broke up, I learned about
all the things he did behind my back.

691
00:38:18,863 --> 00:38:22,318
So after him, even if I date
someone, I don't have that much

692
00:38:22,343 --> 00:38:26,192
feelings for them, and I don't invest
much time and money into them.

693
00:38:27,545 --> 00:38:29,735
(She recalls the painful
memories of those days.)

694
00:38:29,760 --> 00:38:31,230
I think I'm going to cry.

695
00:38:32,630 --> 00:38:33,630
Goodness.

696
00:38:36,581 --> 00:38:40,270
(The wounds of love don't easily go away.)

697
00:38:45,423 --> 00:38:47,716
I really liked him.

698
00:38:52,841 --> 00:38:56,668
(Will they be able to overcome
their past scars and find new love...?)

699
00:38:56,693 --> 00:38:59,315
- They have similar scars.
- Right.

700
00:39:00,368 --> 00:39:04,539
If you think about it, Ha-neul
and Yeo-min are really careful

701
00:39:04,564 --> 00:39:08,197
about approaching people
because of their past wounds.

702
00:39:08,525 --> 00:39:13,496
I think this could be
disadvantageous in the Love Mansion.

703
00:39:13,918 --> 00:39:21,291
Last time, Yeo-min kind of
seemed like a Money Catcher.

704
00:39:21,316 --> 00:39:24,588
But she was just trying not to get hurt,
and I could see why she did that now.

705
00:39:24,613 --> 00:39:26,781
I changed my mind. She's a Love Catcher.

706
00:39:27,363 --> 00:39:30,531
(She's already a true Love
Catcher in Do-yeon's heart.)

707
00:39:30,883 --> 00:39:33,391
On top of that, she
didn't date for five years.

708
00:39:33,416 --> 00:39:34,758
She could be more careful.

709
00:39:37,015 --> 00:39:39,000
What's that? "JH" means...

710
00:39:40,575 --> 00:39:41,575
Jae-hyung?

711
00:39:41,697 --> 00:39:43,633
He has high self-esteem.

712
00:39:43,658 --> 00:39:46,127
(Jae-hyung's cafe exudes
extraordinary presence.)

713
00:39:46,152 --> 00:39:51,172
This is a special space for me, and
honestly, I kind of envied my customers.

714
00:39:51,492 --> 00:39:55,055
I've never had a date in my store.

715
00:39:55,759 --> 00:39:57,814
So this is really special.

716
00:39:59,422 --> 00:40:01,056
That's a drawing of Jae-hyung, too.

717
00:40:02,146 --> 00:40:04,154
- Are you waiting for her?
- Yeah.

718
00:40:04,490 --> 00:40:06,165
- You must be nervous.
- Yeah.

719
00:40:06,723 --> 00:40:08,989
It feels refreshingly
new to have to wait here.

720
00:40:09,273 --> 00:40:10,820
He changed the way
he parted his hair.

721
00:40:10,845 --> 00:40:12,574
I'm curious who she is.

722
00:40:12,824 --> 00:40:18,808
It's our first time talking
alone and going on a date.

723
00:40:20,435 --> 00:40:21,435
So...

724
00:40:23,414 --> 00:40:25,232
Is there a particular meaning behind this?

725
00:40:25,631 --> 00:40:26,631
What's this?

726
00:40:30,065 --> 00:40:31,938
My mouth is growing dry.

727
00:40:32,671 --> 00:40:35,758
Try to charm her! Let
her know you like her!

728
00:40:35,783 --> 00:40:37,285
(Shy)

729
00:40:37,836 --> 00:40:41,018
You have to charm her. She won't
know unless you express your feelings.

730
00:40:41,043 --> 00:40:44,441
Right, you're supposed to express
your feelings for the other person to know.

731
00:40:44,767 --> 00:40:46,382
But that's true though.

732
00:40:46,885 --> 00:40:50,694
Today, when I asked her
out on a date, I wrote a letter.

733
00:40:50,731 --> 00:40:52,016
(You did?)

734
00:40:52,620 --> 00:40:54,886
- Da-Na...
- Oh, that's her name?

735
00:40:54,911 --> 00:40:55,978
- Yes.
- Da-Na.

736
00:40:56,610 --> 00:40:57,974
She's graceful like her name.

737
00:40:59,413 --> 00:41:01,611
(His extravagant rumor makes
them bow their heads.)

738
00:41:01,636 --> 00:41:03,408
She's graceful like her name.

739
00:41:05,815 --> 00:41:07,386
She's graceful, huh?

740
00:41:07,946 --> 00:41:10,573
"Da-Na, I'd like to see
you at a special place."

741
00:41:11,164 --> 00:41:14,934
- I wrote that and gave it to her.
- She doesn't know this is your cafe?

742
00:41:14,959 --> 00:41:15,959
No.

743
00:41:15,984 --> 00:41:19,764
She just thinks it's a cafe.

744
00:41:20,102 --> 00:41:23,254
- Did you remove your picture?
- No, it's still there.

745
00:41:23,279 --> 00:41:24,573
Then she'll find out.

746
00:41:24,829 --> 00:41:26,797
- It's night though.
- Oh, she won't see it?

747
00:41:28,197 --> 00:41:29,197
"Welcome."

748
00:41:31,422 --> 00:41:35,360
Oh, so Su-won is driving her there.

749
00:41:36,476 --> 00:41:39,278
Three guys. So three
guys asked you on a date.

750
00:41:39,565 --> 00:41:40,565
What do I do?

751
00:41:42,687 --> 00:41:44,593
- This is for you.
- Me?

752
00:41:45,485 --> 00:41:46,485
Da-Na.

753
00:41:47,105 --> 00:41:49,462
Jae-hyung actually came into the room?

754
00:41:49,487 --> 00:41:50,907
He came in there himself!

755
00:41:50,932 --> 00:41:52,386
So did Won-jae.

756
00:41:52,952 --> 00:41:54,325
- Yeo-min!
- Yeo-min...

757
00:41:54,634 --> 00:41:58,907
(Da-Na was asked out by three guys.)

758
00:41:59,547 --> 00:42:02,325
It would've been nice if
we could've eaten dinner.

759
00:42:02,542 --> 00:42:05,463
It's fine. You're popular,
so what can we do?

760
00:42:05,488 --> 00:42:06,870
(Sorry)

761
00:42:07,648 --> 00:42:11,095
You'll have to talk with the
others to make up your mind.

762
00:42:11,631 --> 00:42:14,107
I should talk a lot...

763
00:42:15,923 --> 00:42:20,597
- I don't think it'll work out.
- Da-Na feels a wall between them.

764
00:42:21,585 --> 00:42:23,640
Oh, I think that's it.

765
00:42:24,295 --> 00:42:26,120
He's standing there like a mannequin.

766
00:42:26,561 --> 00:42:28,257
Gosh, Jae-hyung is...

767
00:42:28,282 --> 00:42:29,719
(Speechless)

768
00:42:30,334 --> 00:42:31,792
(It's no mannequin.
It's a person.)

769
00:42:32,095 --> 00:42:33,882
(Failed to hold
in their laughter)

770
00:42:33,907 --> 00:42:35,490
How nervous is he?

771
00:42:35,515 --> 00:42:36,911
I really thought he was a doll.

772
00:42:36,936 --> 00:42:39,594
He's not even blinking.

773
00:42:39,619 --> 00:42:42,645
I hope there will be a
woman who thinks that's cute.

774
00:42:42,670 --> 00:42:43,670
Right.

775
00:42:44,653 --> 00:42:50,103
(The one who thinks
this is cute is... Su-won.)

776
00:42:50,807 --> 00:42:52,799
I think you're the only
one who has to get out.

777
00:42:53,595 --> 00:42:55,055
- Have a good time.
- Bye.

778
00:42:56,462 --> 00:42:58,320
(Seeing it again
makes him laugh again.)

779
00:42:58,345 --> 00:42:59,945
- Thanks.
- No problem.

780
00:43:02,691 --> 00:43:05,295
- Hi.
- What's going on?

781
00:43:06,641 --> 00:43:07,641
Let's go in.

782
00:43:08,096 --> 00:43:09,937
Wow, I don't think she saw his picture.

783
00:43:10,424 --> 00:43:13,491
- That's the key point. It's too bad.
- Yeah.

784
00:43:17,700 --> 00:43:19,558
Is this your cafe? Wow, it's nice.

785
00:43:19,583 --> 00:43:21,306
- I rented it for you.
- Really?

786
00:43:21,331 --> 00:43:24,334
(Gold interior that captures
the taste of Jae-hyung)

787
00:43:24,359 --> 00:43:27,255
(A special place where everything
was crafted by Jae-hyung.)

788
00:43:27,280 --> 00:43:29,630
My name is Jung Da-Na.

789
00:43:29,991 --> 00:43:32,301
It's nice to meet you.
I heard a lot about you.

790
00:43:33,846 --> 00:43:36,520
Do you want something
to eat? You're hungry, huh?

791
00:43:36,888 --> 00:43:37,954
Come and choose.

792
00:43:39,352 --> 00:43:41,923
This is the best one.

793
00:43:42,806 --> 00:43:44,315
I want to make this for you.

794
00:43:45,238 --> 00:43:48,008
- That was like a line from a drama.
- "I want to make this for you."

795
00:43:48,033 --> 00:43:50,710
I think he practiced that
while he was waiting for her.

796
00:43:50,735 --> 00:43:54,674
He probably practiced everything, starting
with standing in front of the door.

797
00:43:55,702 --> 00:43:57,749
- Is that you?
- Yeah.

798
00:43:59,491 --> 00:44:02,959
- What are those?
- My fans sent them to me.

799
00:44:03,440 --> 00:44:04,440
Wow, seriously?

800
00:44:04,813 --> 00:44:07,418
He was very cute.
He had milky skin, too.

801
00:44:07,667 --> 00:44:09,714
(She glances between
the pictures and his face.)

802
00:44:09,739 --> 00:44:11,446
I never thought you'd see these.

803
00:44:12,141 --> 00:44:14,474
I was really young and fresh then.

804
00:44:14,499 --> 00:44:16,714
Wow, this is amazing.

805
00:44:17,122 --> 00:44:21,250
It's probably the first time she
found out that he used to be an idol.

806
00:44:23,771 --> 00:44:26,423
- He's making it himself?
- He's making it for her himself.

807
00:44:27,564 --> 00:44:29,097
(Sexy man who can cook)

808
00:44:29,430 --> 00:44:32,832
(This man... What can't he do...?)

809
00:44:33,320 --> 00:44:35,869
- What was your first impression
of him? - First impression?

810
00:44:36,507 --> 00:44:37,641
First impression...

811
00:44:38,404 --> 00:44:41,239
He didn't talk at all,
and he didn't look at me.

812
00:44:41,530 --> 00:44:44,511
(The first day they met)

813
00:44:44,967 --> 00:44:47,459
My name is Seo Jae-hyung,
and I'm 32 years old.

814
00:44:48,241 --> 00:44:49,654
- He was nervous.
- Yeah.

815
00:44:51,610 --> 00:44:53,538
I thought...

816
00:44:54,880 --> 00:44:56,454
he wasn't interested.

817
00:44:57,329 --> 00:45:01,284
- In you?
- Everything, including me.

818
00:45:01,309 --> 00:45:04,556
I thought he wasn't
interested in this situation.

819
00:45:04,632 --> 00:45:06,354
- But after one day...
- He was a comedian?

820
00:45:06,379 --> 00:45:08,069
He suddenly turned into a comedian.

821
00:45:08,778 --> 00:45:10,222
He'd be like, "That's interesting."

822
00:45:10,247 --> 00:45:13,017
- He seems cold at first, right?
- Yes, he does.

823
00:45:15,132 --> 00:45:16,277
(Smile)

824
00:45:17,358 --> 00:45:22,650
- Here's your meal.
- Wow!

825
00:45:22,675 --> 00:45:24,634
- Enjoy.
- What's this? Madeleine?

826
00:45:24,659 --> 00:45:25,659
Yeah.

827
00:45:26,884 --> 00:45:29,685
- Thanks, Jae-hyung.
- Thank you.

828
00:45:30,594 --> 00:45:31,594
Try it.

829
00:45:31,619 --> 00:45:32,714
(Anticipating)

830
00:45:33,131 --> 00:45:35,065
(Stare)

831
00:45:35,835 --> 00:45:37,035
(Glance)

832
00:45:37,748 --> 00:45:38,748
(Uncomfortable)

833
00:45:39,056 --> 00:45:41,795
How can she eat when
you're staring at her?

834
00:45:41,820 --> 00:45:43,915
- Are you gonna watch me?
- No.

835
00:45:44,856 --> 00:45:47,079
- What's wrong with you?
- Why are you doing that?

836
00:45:47,104 --> 00:45:48,842
I'm full even if I don't eat.

837
00:45:48,867 --> 00:45:50,391
He's starting to express himself.

838
00:45:50,416 --> 00:45:51,805
(Embarrassed)

839
00:45:53,670 --> 00:45:55,273
- It's delicious!
- Really?

840
00:45:55,298 --> 00:45:57,243
- It's yummy!
- I put more effort into it.

841
00:45:57,268 --> 00:46:01,118
It's really good. Do you
usually cook the food yourself?

842
00:46:01,671 --> 00:46:08,078
No, I don't. I cooked
especially for you today.

843
00:46:08,240 --> 00:46:09,240
Thanks.

844
00:46:09,638 --> 00:46:12,789
- You really wanted to cook for her.
- Right.

845
00:46:12,814 --> 00:46:15,213
- He's sincere.
- Thank you so much.

846
00:46:17,297 --> 00:46:18,964
And actually...

847
00:46:18,989 --> 00:46:21,316
(Hesitate)

848
00:46:23,718 --> 00:46:28,871
the people I've liked before
have never been here.

849
00:46:29,244 --> 00:46:30,944
It's the first time I
invited a woman here.

850
00:46:31,286 --> 00:46:32,676
"You're the first one."

851
00:46:33,212 --> 00:46:38,023
That's why I wrote that I wanted
to see you in a special place.

852
00:46:38,645 --> 00:46:39,645
I'm honored.

853
00:46:40,217 --> 00:46:41,956
I'm more honored that you came.

854
00:46:42,681 --> 00:46:44,070
(Embarrassed)

855
00:46:44,499 --> 00:46:47,525
- Do you remember this morning?
- Morning? What do you mean?

856
00:46:48,065 --> 00:46:49,532
I asked you something.

857
00:46:50,115 --> 00:46:52,800
(This morning in the common dining room)

858
00:46:52,825 --> 00:46:55,326
What's better? Putting my bangs up or down?

859
00:46:56,099 --> 00:46:59,298
- Up?
- Should I?

860
00:47:00,008 --> 00:47:02,130
Since you said to put them
up, I should put them up.

861
00:47:02,155 --> 00:47:06,052
- Oh my goodness! He's so cute!
- What a cutie.

862
00:47:06,793 --> 00:47:09,207
He did express himself
in the Love Mansion, too.

863
00:47:09,232 --> 00:47:10,958
But I had a hard time,
so I thought I should

864
00:47:10,983 --> 00:47:12,863
just wash my hair and put my bangs down.

865
00:47:12,888 --> 00:47:14,450
- You did it yourself?
- Yeah.

866
00:47:14,475 --> 00:47:17,017
- Really?
- He does everything on his own.

867
00:47:17,042 --> 00:47:19,480
He did all the interior by himself, too.

868
00:47:20,190 --> 00:47:23,390
- He writes songs, too.
- You write songs, too?

869
00:47:23,701 --> 00:47:26,645
- He writes songs, too?
- Yeah, I did it with him.

870
00:47:26,670 --> 00:47:27,895
He released an album.

871
00:47:28,421 --> 00:47:30,214
I added the melody, too.

872
00:47:30,927 --> 00:47:32,460
The song is great, too.

873
00:47:40,732 --> 00:47:44,909
I had no idea that there was
something between you and Won-jae.

874
00:47:44,934 --> 00:47:46,341
- Right.
- But...

875
00:47:48,130 --> 00:47:51,939
Anyway, you missed the timing with Won-jae.

876
00:47:51,964 --> 00:47:56,348
Are you going to try
to win his heart again?

877
00:47:56,607 --> 00:47:58,781
- I don't know what I should do.
- I see.

878
00:47:58,806 --> 00:48:00,330
He could've moved on already.

879
00:48:00,355 --> 00:48:03,793
I met him yesterday to ask him that.

880
00:48:04,902 --> 00:48:06,502
I asked him how he felt.

881
00:48:08,978 --> 00:48:10,676
He didn't give me an exact answer.

882
00:48:11,727 --> 00:48:14,060
- How could he do that?
- Exactly.

883
00:48:16,573 --> 00:48:18,279
That's why I don't know what I should do.

884
00:48:18,739 --> 00:48:20,916
What do you want to do? Just talk with him?

885
00:48:22,038 --> 00:48:26,863
- I think I'm going to keep choosing him.
- She's made up her mind.

886
00:48:29,023 --> 00:48:31,764
I have a lot on my mind, too.

887
00:48:32,022 --> 00:48:33,155
What will you do?

888
00:48:38,099 --> 00:48:42,892
I don't think I'll have he
courage to talk to Su-won.

889
00:48:43,747 --> 00:48:49,518
Him telling me he wants
to get to know others

890
00:48:50,881 --> 00:48:54,382
is different from him actually doing it.

891
00:48:54,407 --> 00:48:56,847
- Right. - It's a different story
after he actually does it.

892
00:48:57,252 --> 00:49:00,166
You must be really curious.
How are you going to ask him?

893
00:49:00,191 --> 00:49:01,844
I don't have the
confidence to ask him.

894
00:49:01,869 --> 00:49:06,687
If he says, "I think I like Da-Na more,"

895
00:49:07,129 --> 00:49:09,820
I really don't think I'll
be able to handle it.

896
00:49:10,146 --> 00:49:11,917
So I'd rather not talk to him about it.

897
00:49:14,820 --> 00:49:17,074
She has a lot going on.

898
00:49:17,099 --> 00:49:20,013
I think Ha-neul has a lot of fear.

899
00:49:20,038 --> 00:49:23,604
I didn't know because she didn't
say it, but she really likes him a lot.

900
00:49:23,629 --> 00:49:25,662
She likes him more deeply than we thought.

901
00:49:26,778 --> 00:49:29,063
But I was scared about
that question yesterday.

902
00:49:29,931 --> 00:49:32,530
When I asked Won-jae
how he felt, I was afraid

903
00:49:32,555 --> 00:49:34,876
he'd firmly tell me he
liked someone else.

904
00:49:35,159 --> 00:49:38,698
- He didn't say that?
- No, so I was relieved.

905
00:49:39,259 --> 00:49:40,925
- I was like that, too.
- Yeah.

906
00:49:41,380 --> 00:49:44,642
If he did say that, then it really means...

907
00:49:46,766 --> 00:49:48,766
that my feelings for him are one-sided.

908
00:49:50,326 --> 00:49:52,627
It's something she knows
but doesn't want to know.

909
00:49:53,449 --> 00:49:54,805
I think to a certain extent...

910
00:49:55,821 --> 00:49:58,226
I'm ready to accept it.

911
00:49:58,454 --> 00:50:00,216
I see. Me, too.

912
00:50:01,676 --> 00:50:03,193
I think I kind of surrendered.

913
00:50:04,135 --> 00:50:05,135
It's not easy.

914
00:50:05,937 --> 00:50:09,671
- Oh no. You shouldn't give up.
- Yeah, it's not over yet.

915
00:50:09,696 --> 00:50:11,139
You shouldn't give up.

916
00:50:11,164 --> 00:50:13,043
(It's a night where they
know where the guys'

917
00:50:13,068 --> 00:50:14,865
hearts are heading
but don't want to know.)

918
00:50:14,890 --> 00:50:17,415
(Meanwhile, one guy is
nervously waiting for someone.)

919
00:50:18,077 --> 00:50:21,140
Why does that pose suit Won-jae?

920
00:50:21,818 --> 00:50:23,421
- Let's take this car.
- Okay.

921
00:50:25,132 --> 00:50:27,148
He's finally taking her
for a ride in this car.

922
00:50:30,677 --> 00:50:37,022
Jae-hyung, how do you feel when everyone
says you're funny back at the dorms?

923
00:50:38,162 --> 00:50:40,806
- I don't usually talk a lot.
- Right.

924
00:50:41,364 --> 00:50:45,271
I've gotten a bit more
comfortable with everyone now.

925
00:50:46,392 --> 00:50:48,137
Do you like being funny?

926
00:50:48,745 --> 00:50:50,316
- Sometimes.
- Really?

927
00:50:50,341 --> 00:50:52,413
I do like being a bit funny.

928
00:50:53,802 --> 00:50:58,750
(While they're talking, another
car passes Jae-hyung's sports car.)

929
00:50:59,677 --> 00:51:02,041
By any chance, is this a
Children Protection Zone?

930
00:51:02,346 --> 00:51:04,941
- You're driving at 30 km/h.
- I usually drive slowly.

931
00:51:04,966 --> 00:51:07,483
- Seriously?
- I usually don't go past 60 km/h.

932
00:51:07,508 --> 00:51:10,176
Why not? You have a car like
this. Then why do you drive it?

933
00:51:11,077 --> 00:51:12,474
I only speed when I need to.

934
00:51:12,715 --> 00:51:13,960
You want me to speed up?

935
00:51:14,312 --> 00:51:17,624
- You're supposed to enjoy
speeding with a car like this. - Right.

936
00:51:17,649 --> 00:51:19,711
You ride it for the thrill.

937
00:51:23,144 --> 00:51:26,996
(For this moment, he leaves his
gentleness behind and explodes with speed.)

938
00:51:27,974 --> 00:51:29,348
Jae-hyung, I'm scared!

939
00:51:30,100 --> 00:51:32,946
(Sincere)

940
00:51:33,727 --> 00:51:35,275
- I'm scared!
- What do you think?

941
00:51:35,300 --> 00:51:36,496
I'm scared!

942
00:51:36,737 --> 00:51:40,399
- You said I was too slow.
- I'm scared. I'm sorry. I take it back.

943
00:51:40,424 --> 00:51:41,925
Let's go 60 km/h.

944
00:51:42,333 --> 00:51:44,086
This is why I drive slowly.

945
00:51:44,755 --> 00:51:46,695
- It's fast, huh?
- Yeah, it's scary.

946
00:51:46,720 --> 00:51:49,393
- This won't do.
- They're a good match.

947
00:51:49,976 --> 00:51:52,776
- This is why I don't drive fast.
- I see.

948
00:51:53,273 --> 00:51:55,804
Won-jae is waiting desperately.

949
00:51:56,934 --> 00:52:00,222
(Jae-hyung & Da-Na appears
with everyone's attention on them.)

950
00:52:00,550 --> 00:52:02,193
- I'll get the door for you.
- Okay.

951
00:52:09,285 --> 00:52:13,433
(The girl he's been
waiting for is here.)

952
00:52:14,373 --> 00:52:15,722
- Bye.
- Bye.

953
00:52:18,880 --> 00:52:20,134
It must've been tough. See you.

954
00:52:20,754 --> 00:52:22,056
"It must've been tough"?

955
00:52:22,805 --> 00:52:25,741
We were on a date!
Why would it have been tough?

956
00:52:28,003 --> 00:52:31,144
(Jae-hyung is alone in his car again.)

957
00:52:32,257 --> 00:52:33,408
- Here?
- Yeah.

958
00:52:38,321 --> 00:52:41,241
- A gym?
- It's where he could show his charms.

959
00:52:43,462 --> 00:52:46,890
I have a lot of memories here.

960
00:52:48,174 --> 00:52:51,259
- It's a meaningful place to me.
- Really?

961
00:52:52,597 --> 00:52:55,486
- Hello.
- Hello.

962
00:52:55,511 --> 00:53:01,858
He helped me get started in fitness.

963
00:53:01,883 --> 00:53:06,863
(They're his coaches who really
helped Won-jae be where he is today.)

964
00:53:07,746 --> 00:53:13,990
(Today, they'll create new memories in
this place filled with Won-jae's memories.)

965
00:53:14,391 --> 00:53:18,458
It's been so long since I heard
he was interested in someone.

966
00:53:21,994 --> 00:53:24,518
- I can see why.
- Thanks.

967
00:53:25,101 --> 00:53:27,172
- Why would you thank him?
- True.

968
00:53:28,533 --> 00:53:30,027
What do you think about Won-jae?

969
00:53:30,578 --> 00:53:31,879
(Flustered)

970
00:53:32,716 --> 00:53:35,390
- He's cute.
- He's more manly than you think.

971
00:53:35,415 --> 00:53:36,615
- Seriously.
- Really?

972
00:53:36,640 --> 00:53:38,228
He's manly and competitive.

973
00:53:38,874 --> 00:53:40,723
He's not really childish.

974
00:53:41,297 --> 00:53:45,638
Really? I like cute guys.

975
00:53:46,937 --> 00:53:48,421
(They failed to make him look good.)

976
00:53:48,446 --> 00:53:50,708
Goodness, this wasn't
what they were aiming for.

977
00:53:52,959 --> 00:53:57,515
He's cute. He is.
You're cute. I totally forgot that.

978
00:53:57,730 --> 00:54:01,005
- How could you forget about that?
- Because I didn't eat yet.

979
00:54:01,442 --> 00:54:02,975
Because it was a given.

980
00:54:03,685 --> 00:54:06,288
- You might as well work out.
- Are you okay with that?

981
00:54:06,313 --> 00:54:07,728
Yeah. I like working out.

982
00:54:08,103 --> 00:54:09,636
Won-jae will teach you.

983
00:54:10,145 --> 00:54:11,867
- I'll teach you something easy.
- Okay.

984
00:54:11,892 --> 00:54:13,741
- Something we can do together.
- Sure.

985
00:54:13,766 --> 00:54:17,442
Oh, that's right. He's
preparing to be a PE teacher.

986
00:54:17,467 --> 00:54:19,270
Show her a demonstration first.

987
00:54:19,694 --> 00:54:21,059
Have you ever done squats before?

988
00:54:21,384 --> 00:54:23,282
Who hasn't done them before?

989
00:54:23,307 --> 00:54:25,833
- Seriously?
- God, that was too much.

990
00:54:26,114 --> 00:54:27,645
What do you take me for?

991
00:54:28,407 --> 00:54:30,920
Of course you did them
before, but in order for them to

992
00:54:30,945 --> 00:54:33,458
be effective, you should do
them in the proper position.

993
00:54:35,464 --> 00:54:36,924
Straighten your back a little.

994
00:54:37,760 --> 00:54:39,046
Go down just like that.

995
00:54:40,344 --> 00:54:41,744
Go up just like that.

996
00:54:42,378 --> 00:54:44,337
(Smiling like parents)

997
00:54:45,371 --> 00:54:47,959
Go down and up just like that.

998
00:54:48,367 --> 00:54:49,767
Don't worry about us.

999
00:54:50,131 --> 00:54:52,171
- Go down.
- You're doing great.

1000
00:54:52,196 --> 00:54:53,744
- You really are.
- Really?

1001
00:54:53,769 --> 00:54:55,619
(Our Won-jae is all grown up now...)

1002
00:54:55,897 --> 00:54:59,027
- Go down again.
- He's wobbling.

1003
00:55:01,119 --> 00:55:02,452
Why are you stumbling?

1004
00:55:03,886 --> 00:55:06,446
If you keep this up, I'll have
to return your training fee.

1005
00:55:06,471 --> 00:55:08,157
He can't focus right now.

1006
00:55:12,497 --> 00:55:14,838
You shouldn't hurt your
knees, so let's stop here.

1007
00:55:14,863 --> 00:55:15,863
Stop here?

1008
00:55:15,888 --> 00:55:18,690
Judging from your posture,
you're much better than Won-jae.

1009
00:55:18,715 --> 00:55:20,128
(Super confident)

1010
00:55:20,153 --> 00:55:22,288
(I'm usually better than this...)

1011
00:55:22,313 --> 00:55:24,347
- Show her your squats.
- Not plain ones.

1012
00:55:24,372 --> 00:55:26,929
Right. You need some weights.

1013
00:55:26,954 --> 00:55:30,830
- Do you need to carry weights?
- No, he'll do squats carrying you.

1014
00:55:32,002 --> 00:55:34,755
- Oh. I have to carry you.
- Really?

1015
00:55:34,780 --> 00:55:37,694
She's light. You've carried
100 kilograms for squats before.

1016
00:55:39,963 --> 00:55:42,858
(He accepts the challenge of
doing squats while carrying Da-Na.)

1017
00:55:42,883 --> 00:55:46,195
You have to hold tightly onto
him so that you won't shake.

1018
00:55:46,656 --> 00:55:47,809
(Squeeze)

1019
00:55:48,732 --> 00:55:50,717
- How many?
- I’ll take care of that.

1020
00:55:51,974 --> 00:55:53,172
Alright, get ready.

1021
00:55:53,197 --> 00:55:55,230
One. You have to go slowly.

1022
00:55:56,239 --> 00:55:58,656
- Hey, why did your face turn red?
- It's not red at all.

1023
00:55:58,990 --> 00:56:01,256
- Am I heavy?
- Pull her in more.

1024
00:56:02,263 --> 00:56:03,263
Three.

1025
00:56:03,288 --> 00:56:05,408
I'm sorry. I shouldn't have eaten dinner.

1026
00:56:07,274 --> 00:56:08,433
He had to push her up.

1027
00:56:09,120 --> 00:56:10,445
They're adorable.

1028
00:56:10,860 --> 00:56:12,057
- Are you okay?
- Yup.

1029
00:56:14,406 --> 00:56:15,895
One.

1030
00:56:16,824 --> 00:56:18,476
Two. Nice.

1031
00:56:19,368 --> 00:56:21,091
- Three.
- Are your knees okay?

1032
00:56:21,124 --> 00:56:22,124
Three.

1033
00:56:23,531 --> 00:56:26,881
Five. Six.

1034
00:56:27,362 --> 00:56:31,044
I'm curious to find out what
Da-Na thought about this date.

1035
00:56:31,069 --> 00:56:34,031
- Okay, there you go. Good job.
- Put me down!

1036
00:56:35,838 --> 00:56:38,878
- Did you have a hard time?
- It was hard for me.

1037
00:56:39,326 --> 00:56:40,326
It was fun.

1038
00:56:40,668 --> 00:56:45,924
For me, it's more
interesting to do active things.

1039
00:56:47,112 --> 00:56:48,422
Don't look at me.

1040
00:56:49,041 --> 00:56:50,827
Oh, she's good at that.

1041
00:56:53,628 --> 00:56:57,127
My ideal type is a cute person.

1042
00:56:57,152 --> 00:57:00,457
He was really trying
hard. It was cute.

1043
00:57:01,710 --> 00:57:06,104
(They're each other's ideal types.
What will happen to them in the future?)

1044
00:57:06,921 --> 00:57:13,120
(The fifth date: In-seong & Jung-woo)

1045
00:57:13,145 --> 00:57:16,830
I wrote a message to In-seong
saying, "Let's go have fun."

1046
00:57:17,735 --> 00:57:20,635
(Last night)

1047
00:57:20,962 --> 00:57:27,752
(Jung-woo's heart that wavered for a
moment went back to its original spot.)

1048
00:57:28,705 --> 00:57:30,685
After the couple photo
shoot, I got curious

1049
00:57:30,710 --> 00:57:32,825
about Da-Na, so I
expressed my interest in her.

1050
00:57:34,075 --> 00:57:37,568
But I kept being conscious
of In-seong even after that,

1051
00:57:37,593 --> 00:57:40,774
so I realized that my
feelings for her are sincere.

1052
00:57:41,575 --> 00:57:44,416
- That's why I changed my vote.
- He was jealous.

1053
00:57:45,444 --> 00:57:49,396
(In-seong checked that
Jung-woo had come back to her.)

1054
00:57:49,980 --> 00:57:53,910
Despite the fact that most guys
chose Da-Na, they chose each other.

1055
00:57:57,371 --> 00:58:00,130
- In-seong?
- Huh?

1056
00:58:00,364 --> 00:58:01,665
Oh, Jung-woo.

1057
00:58:03,556 --> 00:58:05,215
(Shy)

1058
00:58:06,100 --> 00:58:08,885
Thanks.

1059
00:58:09,590 --> 00:58:10,976
- See you later.
- Okay.

1060
00:58:12,043 --> 00:58:14,860
In-seong went through
a lot in the beginning.

1061
00:58:14,991 --> 00:58:16,721
He wrote a cute message.

1062
00:58:17,319 --> 00:58:20,541
"The weather is nice today. Do
you want to go on a date with me?"

1063
00:58:20,566 --> 00:58:22,266
He also added, "Let's run away."

1064
00:58:22,291 --> 00:58:24,553
- It was adorable.
- My heart is fluttering!

1065
00:58:24,887 --> 00:58:27,333
(Cafe Godang)

1066
00:58:27,592 --> 00:58:29,830
- My friend's here, too.
- Seriously?

1067
00:58:30,475 --> 00:58:31,475
Hello.

1068
00:58:32,428 --> 00:58:34,008
- Hello.
- Hello.

1069
00:58:34,033 --> 00:58:36,304
- It's nice to meet you.
- It's nice to meet you.

1070
00:58:36,329 --> 00:58:38,243
I guess they all brought their friends.

1071
00:58:39,008 --> 00:58:41,572
- It feels like he's telling
our fortunes, huh? - Seriously.

1072
00:58:41,597 --> 00:58:42,930
Introduce her to me.

1073
00:58:44,527 --> 00:58:46,609
Introduce her with the
information you know.

1074
00:58:46,634 --> 00:58:51,510
She's 26. She's good at
English. And she's pretty and cute.

1075
00:58:52,197 --> 00:58:53,840
That was a satisfying introduction.

1076
00:58:54,080 --> 00:58:55,080
I agree.

1077
00:58:55,905 --> 00:58:58,619
(Nice job, Jung-woo!)

1078
00:58:58,854 --> 00:59:02,791
- We have so many similarities.
- Seriously.

1079
00:59:02,816 --> 00:59:06,137
He said he wakes up
at 7 a.m., and I do, too.

1080
00:59:06,433 --> 00:59:08,989
Right. We have so many things in common.

1081
00:59:09,014 --> 00:59:12,134
I was seriously shocked. I was
taken aback since the first day.

1082
00:59:12,337 --> 00:59:14,813
Our similarities and styles are so similar.

1083
00:59:15,372 --> 00:59:17,316
- That's right.
- I honestly got goosebumps.

1084
00:59:17,697 --> 00:59:21,724
- That's why I asked you out today.
- It's not easy to meet someone like that.

1085
00:59:22,125 --> 00:59:26,302
- Then what's your ideal type?
- Me? That's straightforward.

1086
00:59:29,046 --> 00:59:33,458
I like someone who thinks
a lot about himself.

1087
00:59:33,483 --> 00:59:36,592
I like it if they take
good care of themselves

1088
00:59:36,775 --> 00:59:39,933
and take a lot of time to self-reflect.

1089
00:59:41,527 --> 00:59:43,051
You're the perfect definition.

1090
00:59:43,496 --> 00:59:45,855
It's a good thing he brought him.
He made the right choice.

1091
00:59:45,880 --> 00:59:48,213
While living together, I realized that...

1092
00:59:48,238 --> 00:59:50,565
- "Living together."
- Oh, I'm sorry! That sounds weird.

1093
00:59:50,590 --> 00:59:52,693
- That was good.
- It's true.

1094
00:59:52,725 --> 00:59:55,247
- That sounded a bit weird...
- What did you realize?

1095
00:59:55,272 --> 00:59:58,891
I realized that he's very loyal.

1096
00:59:59,631 --> 01:00:01,298
He's loyal. You're right.

1097
01:00:01,478 --> 01:00:04,453
Whatever he does, he tries his best,

1098
01:00:04,757 --> 01:00:06,821
and he seems very affectionate.

1099
01:00:07,189 --> 01:00:11,713
And it feels like he takes good
care of the people around him.

1100
01:00:12,463 --> 01:00:14,631
You're right. You really
took careful notes about him.

1101
01:00:14,656 --> 01:00:17,007
Honestly, I was keeping
a careful eye on him.

1102
01:00:17,517 --> 01:00:19,757
- Me?
- Yes. To be honest.

1103
01:00:20,399 --> 01:00:22,066
I'm suddenly embarrassed.

1104
01:00:23,593 --> 01:00:25,252
She's really nice, isn't she?

1105
01:00:25,581 --> 01:00:28,436
- I feel like you're a bad liar.
- I'm really bad at lying.

1106
01:00:28,979 --> 01:00:31,590
I can't make eye contact.
You know what I mean, right?

1107
01:00:32,037 --> 01:00:33,903
- And you stammer.
- Right.

1108
01:00:34,056 --> 01:00:35,056
That's nice.

1109
01:00:37,241 --> 01:00:38,733
You two look great together.

1110
01:00:38,758 --> 01:00:41,847
Doesn't it kind of feel like
they're here to set a wedding date?

1111
01:00:42,558 --> 01:00:44,787
Should I go get some bread?

1112
01:00:45,306 --> 01:00:47,567
- Not sweet ones.
- Not sweet ones? You got it.

1113
01:00:47,592 --> 01:00:49,967
Oh, In-seong is the one who leaves here?

1114
01:00:49,992 --> 01:00:54,311
Oh, even though Jung-woo is a
Money Catcher with a fake identity,

1115
01:00:54,617 --> 01:00:56,085
- he's the real deal.
- Right.

1116
01:00:56,110 --> 01:00:58,801
So he probably wants to
ask his friend for advice.

1117
01:00:59,344 --> 01:01:00,544
What do you think?

1118
01:01:01,664 --> 01:01:03,410
- She's really bubbly.
- Right?

1119
01:01:03,435 --> 01:01:04,435
Yeah.

1120
01:01:04,779 --> 01:01:05,912
She's like light.

1121
01:01:07,075 --> 01:01:08,075
I see.

1122
01:01:08,855 --> 01:01:11,140
That's how I felt when I
saw her for the first time.

1123
01:01:12,661 --> 01:01:15,394
- You like her?
- I do.

1124
01:01:15,585 --> 01:01:16,585
I see.

1125
01:01:16,753 --> 01:01:18,554
- I'm worried because...
- Yeah?

1126
01:01:20,121 --> 01:01:23,676
- I actually picked someone
else in the middle. - Oh.

1127
01:01:24,396 --> 01:01:28,007
After that, I was really bothered.

1128
01:01:30,061 --> 01:01:34,330
Even if we're not partners
for the challenges...

1129
01:01:35,287 --> 01:01:37,645
- You want to take care of her.
- Right, that's how I felt.

1130
01:01:39,546 --> 01:01:42,823
It was fascinating
how people's hearts

1131
01:01:42,848 --> 01:01:46,198
go back and forth
in this short time.

1132
01:01:46,864 --> 01:01:47,864
That's cool.

1133
01:01:47,889 --> 01:01:49,490
He's expressing his true feelings.

1134
01:01:50,016 --> 01:01:52,964
I don't think I can make
hasty judgments.

1135
01:01:53,164 --> 01:01:56,098
And there's also the issue
of whether this is fake or real.

1136
01:01:56,977 --> 01:01:59,382
- Then there's me, too.
- Right. That's all mixed together.

1137
01:01:59,711 --> 01:02:02,767
There's a high possibility that
Jung-woo will change into a Love Catcher.

1138
01:02:06,790 --> 01:02:09,718
Wow, it was really dynamic.

1139
01:02:10,038 --> 01:02:12,372
Another day has passed by.

1140
01:02:13,097 --> 01:02:14,297
It's not over yet.

1141
01:02:14,401 --> 01:02:16,297
It's not over yet.

1142
01:02:16,744 --> 01:02:18,070
It's really not over yet.

1143
01:02:18,333 --> 01:02:20,278
Wow, but there are only two more days left.

1144
01:02:20,714 --> 01:02:22,047
- For real?
- Yeah.

1145
01:02:22,137 --> 01:02:23,537
We're in big trouble.

1146
01:02:24,219 --> 01:02:26,037
Can I ask you something?

1147
01:02:26,910 --> 01:02:27,910
What is it?

1148
01:02:29,281 --> 01:02:30,479
I'm embarrassed.

1149
01:02:32,142 --> 01:02:36,964
I definitely do think that you can be

1150
01:02:36,989 --> 01:02:39,655
interested in and
curious about other girls.

1151
01:02:40,388 --> 01:02:42,500
So I didn't have much expectations.

1152
01:02:43,320 --> 01:02:48,019
So when you knocked on the
door, I was honestly surprised.

1153
01:02:48,554 --> 01:02:49,904
- I see. - Yeah.

1154
01:02:51,639 --> 01:02:53,503
Can I ask you why you chose me?

1155
01:02:54,037 --> 01:02:55,744
Why did I choose you?

1156
01:02:55,917 --> 01:02:56,917
Yeah, like...

1157
01:02:56,942 --> 01:02:58,619
- And not someone else?
- Yeah.

1158
01:02:58,644 --> 01:03:02,813
Besides the first day, we didn't
have the chance to be alone.

1159
01:03:02,838 --> 01:03:05,436
Exactly. We didn't have
the chance to be alone.

1160
01:03:06,142 --> 01:03:07,875
- Oh, that's why?
- Yeah.

1161
01:03:08,967 --> 01:03:10,474
- Really?
- Yeah.

1162
01:03:11,247 --> 01:03:15,860
To be honest, I was kind of
happy that he came to me.

1163
01:03:18,255 --> 01:03:20,095
- Why are you laughing?
- No, it's nothing.

1164
01:03:20,923 --> 01:03:23,566
Just ignore me.

1165
01:03:24,540 --> 01:03:28,561
(As much as they're happy,
their thoughts deepen, too.)

1166
01:03:28,586 --> 01:03:31,574
- So we saw five dates today.
- Right.

1167
01:03:31,599 --> 01:03:34,974
I think there are both successful
and unsuccessful dates.

1168
01:03:34,999 --> 01:03:40,590
I think everyone had a good
time except for Su-won and Da-Na.

1169
01:03:40,615 --> 01:03:45,182
Right. I think she was
very conscious of Ha-neul.

1170
01:03:45,207 --> 01:03:48,076
She looked uncomfortable, and he
seemed uncomfortable watching her.

1171
01:03:48,101 --> 01:03:52,223
Don't you think Su-won realized it
after his date with Da-Na? As expected...

1172
01:03:52,248 --> 01:03:53,438
Ha-neul is the one for him.

1173
01:03:53,463 --> 01:03:56,949
- Will he go back to her now?
- I think he will.

1174
01:03:57,534 --> 01:03:59,811
Aren't you curious how she'll take it?

1175
01:03:59,836 --> 01:04:03,102
Right. When she was
talking with Yeo-min, it

1176
01:04:03,127 --> 01:04:06,610
seemed like she had
pretty much given up on him.

1177
01:04:09,152 --> 01:04:12,164
(Da-na's first date
Su-won comes back.)

1178
01:04:15,977 --> 01:04:19,108
(Su-won slightly glances at
the women's lodging.)

1179
01:04:20,439 --> 01:04:22,621
- Hey.
- You look happy.

1180
01:04:22,749 --> 01:04:24,312
- What?
- You look happy.

1181
01:04:25,395 --> 01:04:26,951
Did you eat something
on the streets?

1182
01:04:27,089 --> 01:04:29,843
I had something at the cafe,
but there was some food leftover.

1183
01:04:29,868 --> 01:04:31,803
- I'm curious how his date went.
- My date?

1184
01:04:33,802 --> 01:04:36,778
So... you don't think Da-Na is the one?

1185
01:04:37,695 --> 01:04:40,036
- We talked for about two to three hours.
- Right.

1186
01:04:41,086 --> 01:04:44,436
After talking with her,
it became clear to me.

1187
01:04:46,681 --> 01:04:49,339
- That it's Ha-neul?
- Yup.

1188
01:04:51,899 --> 01:04:52,899
Really?

1189
01:04:54,324 --> 01:04:57,181
- 100 percent.
- Eventually, he chose Ha-neul.

1190
01:04:59,647 --> 01:05:01,456
I'm curious about what's on Ji-min's mind.

1191
01:05:02,091 --> 01:05:07,959
I thought to myself, "If no one
picks Ha-neul, she'll be alone today."

1192
01:05:09,283 --> 01:05:12,380
But you were curious, so it's
only right that you explore that, too.

1193
01:05:13,408 --> 01:05:14,542
(Sympathizes)

1194
01:05:15,409 --> 01:05:18,855
What do I need to do? Should I
knock on the door and ask her to talk?

1195
01:05:24,331 --> 01:05:26,085
(Perturbed)

1196
01:05:26,874 --> 01:05:29,048
Yeah, I think it's better to talk to her.

1197
01:05:30,955 --> 01:05:34,656
(Now, it's time to unravel the strings
that had been tangled for a long time.)

1198
01:05:38,854 --> 01:05:39,854
But...

1199
01:05:41,108 --> 01:05:42,778
I'm sure she was hurt.

1200
01:05:43,724 --> 01:05:47,295
I don't know how I have to talk to her.

1201
01:05:52,121 --> 01:05:53,121
I'm screwed.

1202
01:05:54,474 --> 01:05:57,531
- It's true that things are twisted.
- Yeah, they're twisted.

1203
01:06:01,650 --> 01:06:05,109
But Ha-neul still likes Su-won.

1204
01:06:05,134 --> 01:06:09,994
Then I think she'll be grateful if
he comes and talks to her first.

1205
01:06:10,019 --> 01:06:11,019
Right.

1206
01:06:11,842 --> 01:06:13,143
I'm back.

1207
01:06:14,280 --> 01:06:15,280
Hey.

1208
01:06:15,694 --> 01:06:18,360
- How was it?
- I brought presents.

1209
01:06:18,651 --> 01:06:20,891
- What's that?
- What's that? You really did?

1210
01:06:21,021 --> 01:06:23,808
Since you couldn't go on
dates, I brought you gifts.

1211
01:06:23,888 --> 01:06:25,731
I can't really see well. What is it?

1212
01:06:25,756 --> 01:06:28,672
It's cake and drinks
from the cafe we went to.

1213
01:06:28,697 --> 01:06:29,697
Awesome!

1214
01:06:33,328 --> 01:06:36,010
- She's like light.
- How was it? Sit down.

1215
01:06:37,237 --> 01:06:39,038
How was it? Was it nice?

1216
01:06:40,733 --> 01:06:44,145
There was someone
unexpected at our date.

1217
01:06:44,785 --> 01:06:48,388
I met someone who's been
friends with Jung-woo for 20 years.

1218
01:06:49,225 --> 01:06:51,161
- Really? That's crazy.
- Yeah.

1219
01:06:51,186 --> 01:06:53,061
I could tell they were really good friends.

1220
01:06:54,502 --> 01:06:58,020
- Did you have a good time with him?
- Yeah, I did.

1221
01:06:58,450 --> 01:07:01,474
- Did your feelings for him grow?
- Honestly, yes.

1222
01:07:02,598 --> 01:07:04,573
That's why things are complicated, huh?

1223
01:07:04,598 --> 01:07:06,076
Aww, aww.

1224
01:07:06,101 --> 01:07:08,473
- Surprisingly, you two are a good fit.
- Yeah.

1225
01:07:09,187 --> 01:07:11,302
(In-seong seems to be
locked in her thoughts.)

1226
01:07:11,327 --> 01:07:13,392
- Are you okay?
- Yeah, I'm just...

1227
01:07:14,034 --> 01:07:15,362
starting to have
a lot on my mind.

1228
01:07:15,387 --> 01:07:17,387
Why? Didn't thinks get easier?

1229
01:07:17,733 --> 01:07:22,027
Once you start liking someone,
there's the thing you need to think about.

1230
01:07:22,386 --> 01:07:24,609
Is he a Love Catcher or Money Catcher?

1231
01:07:24,634 --> 01:07:25,802
That's right.

1232
01:07:25,827 --> 01:07:28,653
The more you like someone,
the more complex it gets.

1233
01:07:28,678 --> 01:07:31,657
Things could get complicated
if she's a Money Catcher, too.

1234
01:07:31,682 --> 01:07:34,869
Maybe she feels sorry as a Money Catcher
because he seems genuinely into her.

1235
01:07:35,235 --> 01:07:38,164
- Did you have fun?
- It was alright.

1236
01:07:38,923 --> 01:07:40,922
Did you come to a clear decision?

1237
01:07:43,033 --> 01:07:44,166
- No.
- Why not?

1238
01:07:44,815 --> 01:07:46,260
What makes you say that?

1239
01:07:46,570 --> 01:07:48,165
(Curious)

1240
01:07:49,925 --> 01:07:52,338
I thought, "He might
not see me as a woman."

1241
01:07:52,363 --> 01:07:53,951
Seriously? Why?

1242
01:07:54,565 --> 01:07:56,970
Ji-min said he's cautious
because we're 9 years apart.

1243
01:07:57,886 --> 01:08:00,266
- Of course he's cautious.
- Of course he is.

1244
01:08:00,363 --> 01:08:05,509
But he said other things, too, and
this is the conclusion that I came to.

1245
01:08:06,893 --> 01:08:08,426
- Really?
- Oh my god.

1246
01:08:09,350 --> 01:08:12,502
I thought, "Even if I'm
straightforward, it'll be pointless."

1247
01:08:16,326 --> 01:08:20,612
I think, based on his standards, it'll be
difficult for him to overcome our age gap.

1248
01:08:23,858 --> 01:08:25,811
Everyone should make
choices they won't regret.

1249
01:08:26,583 --> 01:08:29,583
- She just happened to be born that year.
- What could she do?

1250
01:08:30,103 --> 01:08:31,872
He's too focused on the age part.

1251
01:08:32,256 --> 01:08:38,147
Then what about Ahn Ji-min? Do you
think he has feelings for Yang Ji-min now?

1252
01:08:38,343 --> 01:08:40,326
I don't know.

1253
01:08:40,644 --> 01:08:44,537
During the date, it seemed like they were
expressing their interests in each other.

1254
01:08:44,984 --> 01:08:48,366
But Yang Ji-min said her
feelings became more complicated.

1255
01:08:48,391 --> 01:08:52,445
Is Ahn Ji-min a Money Catcher
who can't proactively reach his

1256
01:08:52,470 --> 01:08:56,523
goal because he fell for Ha-neul
and doesn't want to hurt her?

1257
01:08:56,548 --> 01:08:58,289
- Right. That's possible.
- I think so, too.

1258
01:08:58,314 --> 01:09:01,647
Oh, because he's a Money
Catcher? That might be the case.

1259
01:09:02,555 --> 01:09:04,777
(Men's lodging)

1260
01:09:05,977 --> 01:09:09,298
(Su-won is stuck in his dilemma.)

1261
01:09:11,161 --> 01:09:13,541
Go to Ha-neul. Go tell her.

1262
01:09:16,224 --> 01:09:17,422
That's right. You must go.

1263
01:09:17,447 --> 01:09:21,314
You have to go. There's no
time. There are only two days left.

1264
01:09:21,339 --> 01:09:23,848
(Will he be able to tell
Ha-neul how he feels?)

1265
01:09:25,222 --> 01:09:27,352
(Glance)

1266
01:09:31,638 --> 01:09:33,495
I'm curious how you two spent the day.

1267
01:09:33,520 --> 01:09:35,822
- We had cocktail on a rooftop.
- We had cocktail.

1268
01:09:35,847 --> 01:09:39,530
- Really? That sounds fun.
- No one was there.

1269
01:09:39,555 --> 01:09:42,057
(Ha-neul spots Su-won.)

1270
01:09:42,401 --> 01:09:43,774
(Fake laugh)

1271
01:09:44,504 --> 01:09:46,348
She can't control her expression.

1272
01:09:46,661 --> 01:09:47,661
(Glance)

1273
01:09:50,297 --> 01:09:53,564
(The dining room falls
silent at his appearance.)

1274
01:09:53,931 --> 01:09:55,843
Why are you doing the dishes alone?

1275
01:09:55,868 --> 01:09:57,351
You didn't tell her yet, did you?

1276
01:09:57,376 --> 01:09:59,219
No, I didn't.

1277
01:10:00,413 --> 01:10:03,183
(He can't bring himself
to go to the dining room.)

1278
01:10:03,933 --> 01:10:05,790
- Just slide in and talk to her.
- What?

1279
01:10:05,956 --> 01:10:07,378
Just slide in and talk to her.

1280
01:10:08,062 --> 01:10:09,062
Later.

1281
01:10:09,834 --> 01:10:11,486
Depending on the situation.

1282
01:10:12,149 --> 01:10:14,578
- Yes.
- You must muster up the courage.

1283
01:10:14,603 --> 01:10:17,071
(Ha-neul approaches Su-won.)

1284
01:10:22,307 --> 01:10:23,967
(He sits near her.)

1285
01:10:28,700 --> 01:10:31,110
(He's looking for the
perfect time to talk to her.)

1286
01:10:31,916 --> 01:10:35,495
(As if planned ahead, the
dining room grows silent again.)

1287
01:10:37,412 --> 01:10:39,135
(Concerned)

1288
01:10:39,948 --> 01:10:41,868
- I'm gonna use the restroom.
- Okay.

1289
01:10:43,133 --> 01:10:45,911
- He's leaving on purpose.
- He's doing it on purpose.

1290
01:10:47,099 --> 01:10:49,161
(Su-won keeps searching
for the right moment.)

1291
01:10:50,934 --> 01:10:53,467
- The atmosphere...
- Ugh, it's cold.

1292
01:10:54,040 --> 01:10:55,429
(Careful)

1293
01:10:56,409 --> 01:10:58,083
- Did you get that today?
- It's cocktail.

1294
01:10:58,108 --> 01:11:00,067
- It is?
- Yeah. It's good.

1295
01:11:00,793 --> 01:11:01,793
(Glance)

1296
01:11:01,818 --> 01:11:04,128
- The rooftop was gorgeous.
- It was absolutely stunning.

1297
01:11:04,153 --> 01:11:06,258
- You haven't been there, huh?
- No, not even once.

1298
01:11:06,283 --> 01:11:09,210
- I'm so jealous. - We went there.
The sunset was pretty, too.

1299
01:11:09,235 --> 01:11:11,119
The only thing missing were men.

1300
01:11:13,742 --> 01:11:15,876
(Bitter)

1301
01:11:17,014 --> 01:11:19,849
What did you do during the
rest of the time we weren't here?

1302
01:11:20,130 --> 01:11:22,885
We just... I'm not sure what we did.

1303
01:11:26,845 --> 01:11:28,378
You went through a lot.

1304
01:11:29,082 --> 01:11:31,967
(His guilt towards Ha-neul
becomes bigger and bigger.)

1305
01:11:32,691 --> 01:11:33,691
It's cold.

1306
01:11:35,870 --> 01:11:38,570
(The coldest thing
is Ha-neul's heart.)

1307
01:11:39,271 --> 01:11:40,824
(Tell her.)

1308
01:11:42,179 --> 01:11:44,345
Jung-woo keeps telling him to do it.

1309
01:11:48,535 --> 01:11:50,455
- Tell her!
- Come on.

1310
01:11:52,635 --> 01:11:55,325
Will they give us time to
check our lockers today?

1311
01:11:56,248 --> 01:11:59,066
- I don't want to check.
- We might not get to today.

1312
01:12:02,224 --> 01:12:03,565
(I see...)

1313
01:12:07,950 --> 01:12:08,950
She's leaving!

1314
01:12:09,755 --> 01:12:12,302
- Go after her!
- Follow her.

1315
01:12:13,791 --> 01:12:16,426
- Go with her.
- Go after her.

1316
01:12:17,319 --> 01:12:18,819
- He's not going?
- Oh, man.

1317
01:12:19,676 --> 01:12:20,970
(Frustrated)

1318
01:12:21,568 --> 01:12:23,878
(Su-won has no idea what to do...)

1319
01:12:23,903 --> 01:12:26,579
(and the girls are sitting
on pins and needles.)

1320
01:12:27,105 --> 01:12:29,377
(Jung-woo, who is watching,
feels frustrated, too.)

1321
01:12:30,605 --> 01:12:32,601
(How should he express his feelings?)

1322
01:12:32,626 --> 01:12:35,034
What should he say first?

1323
01:12:35,601 --> 01:12:38,013
I think that's the biggest
concern for him right now.

1324
01:12:38,038 --> 01:12:40,697
Right. Once they get started,
they'll be able to resolve

1325
01:12:40,730 --> 01:12:43,805
the misunderstandings and
confirm each other's feelings.

1326
01:12:43,830 --> 01:12:45,053
It all depends on Su-won.

1327
01:12:45,078 --> 01:12:46,579
- Exactly.
- Yes, you're right.

1328
01:12:46,604 --> 01:12:48,335
He has to make the first move!

1329
01:12:51,061 --> 01:12:54,512
(Won-jae, who was Da-na's
last date, came back...)

1330
01:12:54,537 --> 01:12:56,739
Did you see any signals between you two?

1331
01:12:57,330 --> 01:13:00,735
We were both pretty tired.

1332
01:13:00,760 --> 01:13:02,824
On top of that, she was out the whole day.

1333
01:13:03,328 --> 01:13:05,467
It could've been a bit
uncomfortable to work

1334
01:13:05,492 --> 01:13:07,535
out, but she enjoyed
it without complaints.

1335
01:13:07,893 --> 01:13:09,249
It was an enjoyable date.

1336
01:13:10,438 --> 01:13:11,438
What about you?

1337
01:13:11,463 --> 01:13:16,188
It was a chance where I could confirm
my feelings, so I think it was great.

1338
01:13:16,930 --> 01:13:18,811
- Where did you go, Ji-min?
- Me?

1339
01:13:18,836 --> 01:13:20,757
Yeah. Who'd you go on a date with?

1340
01:13:20,991 --> 01:13:23,014
- Ji-min.
- Oh.

1341
01:13:23,332 --> 01:13:26,117
You were with Ji-min?
I thought you were with Ha-neul.

1342
01:13:26,512 --> 01:13:29,075
- Won-jae's asking him this?
- Why did he think it was Ha-neul?

1343
01:13:29,100 --> 01:13:32,863
- Everyone keeps seeing them together.
- That's right.

1344
01:13:32,888 --> 01:13:34,446
So it's natural he thinks that way.

1345
01:13:34,799 --> 01:13:37,457
- I thought you were with Ha-neul.
- Me? Why?

1346
01:13:38,068 --> 01:13:39,068
Just.

1347
01:13:40,000 --> 01:13:42,637
Just. I had a lunch. I
thought you were with her.

1348
01:13:42,828 --> 01:13:45,203
- Why?
- Either Ha-neul or Da-Na.

1349
01:13:45,236 --> 01:13:47,173
- Why Ha-neul though?
- Just.

1350
01:13:48,049 --> 01:13:50,914
- What? I was with Ji-min.
- Ji-min came by this morning.

1351
01:13:51,559 --> 01:13:53,791
Oh, so the one you
mentioned earlier was Ji-min.

1352
01:13:56,766 --> 01:13:58,567
Start from your first date.

1353
01:13:58,919 --> 01:14:01,348
- I'll give you brief summaries.
- Who was your first date?

1354
01:14:01,373 --> 01:14:03,610
- Su-won?
- Yes, Su-won.

1355
01:14:03,635 --> 01:14:06,463
(One person isn't too
pleased with this story.)

1356
01:14:06,488 --> 01:14:08,155
- It was awkward.
- Why?

1357
01:14:08,346 --> 01:14:09,595
It was somewhat awkward.

1358
01:14:09,620 --> 01:14:11,811
You both aren't the type to
be awkward around anyone.

1359
01:14:11,964 --> 01:14:13,035
- Really?
- Yeah.

1360
01:14:13,060 --> 01:14:14,379
Your conversation didn't flow?

1361
01:14:14,404 --> 01:14:16,927
How do I put...?

1362
01:14:17,614 --> 01:14:19,748
Our conversation didn't really play out.

1363
01:14:20,180 --> 01:14:21,481
It's because of Ha-neul.

1364
01:14:22,452 --> 01:14:28,410
Jae-hyung was really,
really, really good to me.

1365
01:14:28,435 --> 01:14:30,617
- He even cooked dinner for me.
- He cooked it himself?

1366
01:14:30,642 --> 01:14:32,358
- Really?
- He cooked and...

1367
01:14:32,607 --> 01:14:37,471
But overall, I had the
most fun with Won-jae.

1368
01:14:38,373 --> 01:14:39,373
Oh dear.

1369
01:14:40,129 --> 01:14:41,875
- Did you work out?
- Yes.

1370
01:14:41,900 --> 01:14:43,765
I did this, too.

1371
01:14:43,790 --> 01:14:45,379
Wow, I love that. Lifts.

1372
01:14:45,508 --> 01:14:47,769
Won-jae even did that
with me sitting on top of him!

1373
01:14:49,138 --> 01:14:51,380
(Da-Na joined on the
second day, so she had no

1374
01:14:51,405 --> 01:14:53,647
idea about Yeo-min and
Won-jae's relationship.)

1375
01:14:56,024 --> 01:14:57,548
(What about you, In-seong?)

1376
01:14:58,124 --> 01:15:00,004
Did you have a good time?
How was it?

1377
01:15:00,102 --> 01:15:03,484
How do I put it? The cafe
was designed like a hanok.

1378
01:15:03,509 --> 01:15:06,899
I liked the atmosphere
that was like the night view.

1379
01:15:07,220 --> 01:15:09,228
Why aren't you bringing
up the important stuff?

1380
01:15:09,828 --> 01:15:11,228
(Important stuff...?)

1381
01:15:11,367 --> 01:15:12,883
You said you started to like him.

1382
01:15:14,768 --> 01:15:17,626
- You did?
- Yes, a little

1383
01:15:19,769 --> 01:15:22,846
(Da-Na, who expressed her interest
in Jung-woo, tries hard to smile.)

1384
01:15:23,356 --> 01:15:24,737
(Shy)

1385
01:15:24,762 --> 01:15:26,911
They have a lot in common, too.

1386
01:15:28,633 --> 01:15:35,175
Even though they don't say it, they
know who likes the person that they like.

1387
01:15:35,473 --> 01:15:38,744
- So to the other person...
- They're a bit careful.

1388
01:15:40,493 --> 01:15:41,692
- I'm hungry.
- What's that?

1389
01:15:44,181 --> 01:15:46,248
I think it's about the lockers.

1390
01:15:48,081 --> 01:15:49,615
What will happen today?

1391
01:15:50,783 --> 01:15:52,901
- Oh my god!
- Oh, that scared me!

1392
01:15:55,430 --> 01:15:57,636
(Tonight...)

1393
01:15:58,196 --> 01:16:00,648
- "Tonight..."
- Something's up.

1394
01:16:01,324 --> 01:16:02,634
(What is it?)

1395
01:16:03,931 --> 01:16:04,931
What is it?

1396
01:16:05,178 --> 01:16:06,311
What's happening?

1397
01:16:08,589 --> 01:16:13,691
(Tonight, someone will get eliminated.)

1398
01:16:15,134 --> 01:16:16,134
No way!

1399
01:16:16,587 --> 01:16:18,627
I think they must've been really shocked.

1400
01:16:19,504 --> 01:16:21,012
- What the heck?
- Oh my god!

1401
01:16:21,037 --> 01:16:22,037
Wait a minute.

1402
01:16:22,435 --> 01:16:24,268
Isn't this something
we never expected?

1403
01:16:25,049 --> 01:16:26,049
Right.

1404
01:16:26,074 --> 01:16:27,898
What are the standards for elimination?

1405
01:16:28,937 --> 01:16:32,951
(Please vote who you
suspect is a Money Catcher.)

1406
01:16:32,976 --> 01:16:35,145
Wow. Today's so...

1407
01:16:35,607 --> 01:16:37,521
My heart is beating really fast right now.

1408
01:16:38,243 --> 01:16:39,941
They must be so extremely nervous.

1409
01:16:43,600 --> 01:16:45,553
I might end up going home today.

1410
01:16:46,024 --> 01:16:49,976
But I don't even know
which girl to vote for.

1411
01:16:51,464 --> 01:16:52,742
I think I'll end up going home.

1412
01:16:52,767 --> 01:16:54,094
One man and one woman?

1413
01:16:54,119 --> 01:16:55,808
- That's cruel.
- It's cruel.

1414
01:16:57,459 --> 01:17:01,610
You could be eliminated or the
one you like can be eliminated.

1415
01:17:01,635 --> 01:17:02,635
Right.

1416
01:17:04,541 --> 01:17:06,474
They're on their way to vote.

1417
01:17:08,397 --> 01:17:10,238
I don't think they'll be able to do it.

1418
01:17:10,263 --> 01:17:13,652
(Their footsteps are
much heavier than usual.)

1419
01:17:13,677 --> 01:17:18,386
(Who will they choose?)

1420
01:17:20,101 --> 01:17:22,195
Is there anyone you thought
was a Money Catcher?

1421
01:17:22,627 --> 01:17:26,484
I actually thought a lot about it.
It's either Yeo-min or In-seong.

1422
01:17:26,718 --> 01:17:28,646
I kind of thought Yeo-min was one.

1423
01:17:28,950 --> 01:17:31,578
- In-seong or Yeo-min.
- I guess he was deducing it.

1424
01:17:34,879 --> 01:17:40,458
After today's date, I was certain
that she was a Money Catcher.

1425
01:17:41,064 --> 01:17:43,074
- After today's date?
- So it's Da-Na?

1426
01:17:43,099 --> 01:17:44,099
Da-Na?

1427
01:17:47,097 --> 01:17:49,740
I think Da-na's a Money Catcher.

1428
01:17:50,654 --> 01:17:52,419
People are suspecting Da-Na.

1429
01:17:52,444 --> 01:17:56,141
- She's being suspected a lot.
- She started to like Won-jae.

1430
01:17:58,482 --> 01:18:00,577
- I feel really bad.
- Right?

1431
01:18:01,428 --> 01:18:04,962
- Does your heart feel heavy?
- I couldn't press it.

1432
01:18:05,489 --> 01:18:07,671
- It makes your heart
heavier than expected. - Yeah.

1433
01:18:08,977 --> 01:18:10,596
I feel so bad. What do I do?

1434
01:18:14,030 --> 01:18:15,982
Which girl do you think is a Money Catcher?

1435
01:18:16,166 --> 01:18:17,857
I didn't get any vibes like that at all.

1436
01:18:17,882 --> 01:18:20,979
Maybe I wasn't conscious
of it, but I didn't feel it.

1437
01:18:21,818 --> 01:18:24,076
(Anguished)

1438
01:18:25,118 --> 01:18:27,780
(After much thinking, who did he choose?)

1439
01:18:30,897 --> 01:18:33,936
I don't think I can make
hasty judgments.

1440
01:18:34,139 --> 01:18:37,360
And there's also the issue
of whether this is fake or real.

1441
01:18:38,149 --> 01:18:41,127
He does like In-seong, but
he's confused about her identity.

1442
01:18:41,455 --> 01:18:44,171
But I still don't think he'll choose her.

1443
01:18:49,138 --> 01:18:51,408
Honestly, in my opinion,
Ha-neul seems like...

1444
01:18:53,757 --> 01:18:54,967
a Love Catcher.

1445
01:18:56,042 --> 01:18:57,740
That's why I went for her.

1446
01:18:57,910 --> 01:18:59,592
They don't suspect her at all.

1447
01:18:59,617 --> 01:19:02,292
It'd be nice if she could prove them wrong.

1448
01:19:03,238 --> 01:19:04,650
That'd be a twist.

1449
01:19:06,331 --> 01:19:11,982
(After the guys, the girls start voting.)

1450
01:19:13,561 --> 01:19:15,156
Everyone's footsteps are heavy.

1451
01:19:15,181 --> 01:19:19,405
(Who is the man they're
suspecting the most?)

1452
01:19:22,325 --> 01:19:25,952
When I talk with Su-won, I don't
feel certain that he's a Love Catcher.

1453
01:19:26,219 --> 01:19:28,566
Is it because you're suspecting
he's a Money Catcher?

1454
01:19:28,591 --> 01:19:31,085
I thought that at first. I've
thought that since day one.

1455
01:19:31,110 --> 01:19:33,970
(Ha-neul has suspected
Su-won from the beginning.)

1456
01:19:34,559 --> 01:19:39,997
When we first talked at the bar, I
thought he might be a Money Catcher.

1457
01:19:41,669 --> 01:19:45,526
(On the first day, Ji-min
came across three men.)

1458
01:19:46,103 --> 01:19:48,682
I think Su-won is the Money Catcher.

1459
01:19:48,892 --> 01:19:51,567
His proactive attitude
made them think that way.

1460
01:19:53,413 --> 01:19:54,998
(Upset)

1461
01:19:55,694 --> 01:19:57,094
Do I need to pack up?

1462
01:19:57,831 --> 01:20:00,640
I know I got one vote.
Yeo-min definitely voted for me.

1463
01:20:00,665 --> 01:20:02,373
Gosh, don't say that.

1464
01:20:02,756 --> 01:20:07,551
During my night date with
Jung-woo, I realized this.

1465
01:20:07,745 --> 01:20:11,412
For a travel writer, he
couldn't tell me much about it.

1466
01:20:11,782 --> 01:20:15,114
Wow, they all think
about those things, too.

1467
01:20:15,139 --> 01:20:18,182
- On top of that, she's discussing
it with In-seong. - You're right.

1468
01:20:18,207 --> 01:20:20,201
Out of all people. Jeez.

1469
01:20:21,387 --> 01:20:23,403
The girls probably feel the same way, huh?

1470
01:20:23,436 --> 01:20:26,405
- In-seong is probably crying.
- She's about to.

1471
01:20:26,664 --> 01:20:28,410
This is so hard.

1472
01:20:29,362 --> 01:20:31,933
I seriously can't tell.
I have no idea who it is.

1473
01:20:32,582 --> 01:20:34,487
It must be really hard.

1474
01:20:34,512 --> 01:20:35,926
(With a sigh, she picks someone.)

1475
01:20:35,951 --> 01:20:39,800
He's the only one I strongly
believe is a Money Catcher.

1476
01:20:41,052 --> 01:20:43,353
There's someone she's
sure is a Money Catcher?

1477
01:20:43,378 --> 01:20:45,832
(Who is the Money Catcher
that Da-Na is certain of?)

1478
01:20:46,280 --> 01:20:51,094
- What's going on? - The voting for
the eliminated participants have started.

1479
01:20:51,789 --> 01:20:55,861
The key here is that it's not a real
Money Catcher who's being eliminated.

1480
01:20:56,015 --> 01:20:58,547
It's someone who's
suspected of being one.

1481
01:20:58,749 --> 01:21:05,282
Earlier, Jae-hyung said he doesn't
think Ha-neul is a Money Catcher.

1482
01:21:05,307 --> 01:21:12,093
And just then, Su-won quietly
said, "That's why I chose her."

1483
01:21:12,244 --> 01:21:14,111
That's why I went for her.

1484
01:21:14,136 --> 01:21:18,503
He could've said that
because he truly likes her,

1485
01:21:18,952 --> 01:21:24,898
but I think it's possible that he said
that because he's a Money Catcher.

1486
01:21:25,158 --> 01:21:28,038
Personally, I don't think that
Yeo-min is a Money Catcher.

1487
01:21:28,177 --> 01:21:31,708
She's never really proactively
expressed her liking for someone.

1488
01:21:31,991 --> 01:21:38,784
So I think that's why the
guys might think she's one.

1489
01:21:40,388 --> 01:21:43,332
I think it's Yeo-min and Jae-hyung.

1490
01:21:43,357 --> 01:21:45,859
- Oh. Why?
- She won too many challenges.

1491
01:21:46,864 --> 01:21:51,714
I think people keep her in check
while also keeping an eye on her.

1492
01:21:51,739 --> 01:21:53,574
That's why I think
people would suspect her.

1493
01:21:53,599 --> 01:21:57,076
I also think Jae-hyung made
the girls wonder, "Who is he?

1494
01:21:57,101 --> 01:22:00,458
Why isn't he so immersed in
this? Is he a Money Catcher?"

1495
01:22:00,843 --> 01:22:03,192
Hence, I choose these two.

1496
01:22:03,508 --> 01:22:06,480
At first, Ji-min came
to the Love Mansion to

1497
01:22:06,505 --> 01:22:09,740
faithfully carry out his
duty as a Money Catcher.

1498
01:22:09,765 --> 01:22:13,633
But it seems like he's suffering a lot
because he found someone he really likes.

1499
01:22:13,658 --> 01:22:15,970
I think the participants
could've felt that as well.

1500
01:22:18,032 --> 01:22:20,626
I think Da-Na got eliminated.

1501
01:22:20,651 --> 01:22:24,864
It's because those who
went on a date with her might

1502
01:22:24,889 --> 01:22:29,181
rather send her away then
let her be with another guy.

1503
01:22:29,206 --> 01:22:32,034
- That's what I thought.
- Because she's so popular.

1504
01:22:33,214 --> 01:22:35,308
I have a similar reason for Da-Na.

1505
01:22:35,479 --> 01:22:37,711
She's friendly to everyone, so the guys

1506
01:22:37,736 --> 01:22:39,917
might think she treats
everyone the same way.

1507
01:22:39,942 --> 01:22:43,142
Hence, I believe she could be
suspect as a Money Catcher.

1508
01:22:43,606 --> 01:22:45,873
As for the guy, I choose Jung-woo.

1509
01:22:45,905 --> 01:22:48,465
Yeah, I was worried he
might get eliminated, too.

1510
01:22:48,490 --> 01:22:50,976
What Yeo-min said earlier...

1511
01:22:51,278 --> 01:22:55,043
For a travel writer, he
couldn't tell me much about it.

1512
01:22:55,451 --> 01:22:58,486
I believe this wasn't
his first doubtful action.

1513
01:22:58,855 --> 01:23:01,180
So I think that affected this a lot.

1514
01:23:02,064 --> 01:23:03,064
That's likely.

1515
01:23:03,400 --> 01:23:09,730
I think Jae-hyung and
Da-Na will be eliminated.

1516
01:23:09,755 --> 01:23:15,769
First off, Jae-hyung is using things
like his photos as props in his cafe.

1517
01:23:16,396 --> 01:23:18,253
It could've been too much.

1518
01:23:18,278 --> 01:23:21,121
Yes, so I'm pretty much
sure he'll be eliminated.

1519
01:23:21,146 --> 01:23:23,379
I chose Da-Na because...

1520
01:23:23,403 --> 01:23:25,793
I really want a coin this time.

1521
01:23:26,845 --> 01:23:32,282
Ji-min and
Su-won are suspecting her,

1522
01:23:32,874 --> 01:23:35,215
so probability-wise, it's probably her.

1523
01:23:38,245 --> 01:23:42,317
- All right. - Oh, but there
are no overlapping answers today.

1524
01:23:42,342 --> 01:23:44,305
- That's true.
- They're all different.

1525
01:23:44,330 --> 01:23:47,286
Since there are two
people getting eliminated,

1526
01:23:47,532 --> 01:23:50,064
you will receive one
coin per right answer.

1527
01:23:51,649 --> 01:23:54,894
So it's possible for
someone to get two coins.

1528
01:23:54,919 --> 01:23:57,514
Shall we check the answers?

1529
01:23:58,207 --> 01:24:01,355
(The eliminated participants who will
leave the Love Mansion will be unveiled.)

1530
01:24:01,543 --> 01:24:05,040
(With heavy footsteps, the 10
participants head to the Room of Secrets.)

1531
01:24:05,463 --> 01:24:07,892
(Room of Secrets)

1532
01:24:11,598 --> 01:24:15,381
(Some will stay, some will go.)

1533
01:24:15,903 --> 01:24:18,539
It's the heaviest time
ever since they got here.

1534
01:24:18,564 --> 01:24:22,860
(If I or the person I'm
interested in will have to leave...)

1535
01:24:24,143 --> 01:24:28,842
(They can't say anything at this moment.)

1536
01:24:32,834 --> 01:24:35,438
- Oh, right away?
- I can't watch!

1537
01:24:35,463 --> 01:24:39,448
(Can they find the
true Money Catchers?)

1538
01:24:39,473 --> 01:24:42,016
(Revealing the Eliminated Participants)

1539
01:24:46,359 --> 01:24:49,111
(Before the announcement, Jung-woo
couldn't hide his nervousness.)

1540
01:24:49,136 --> 01:24:52,963
- I feel like it'll be me.
- I think it's me.

1541
01:24:54,255 --> 01:24:56,041
You really took careful notes about him.

1542
01:24:56,066 --> 01:24:58,089
Honestly, I was keeping
a careful eye on him.

1543
01:24:58,114 --> 01:25:00,823
(Through today's date, his
feelings for In-seong grew bigger.)

1544
01:25:01,682 --> 01:25:04,661
(In-seong felt the same way as well.)

1545
01:25:05,534 --> 01:25:10,464
(That's why he's more nervous and anxious.)

1546
01:25:11,287 --> 01:25:12,914
(Nervous)

1547
01:25:18,913 --> 01:25:23,480
(They can't help but wait
while holding their breaths.)

1548
01:25:25,457 --> 01:25:28,457
(Yoon Jung-woo & Yang
Ji-min are eliminated.)

1549
01:25:33,526 --> 01:25:34,526
Oh my goodness!

1550
01:25:35,144 --> 01:25:36,811
That is definitely not what I expected.

1551
01:25:42,820 --> 01:25:47,440
(Yoon Jung-woo & Yang
Ji-min are eliminated.)

1552
01:25:49,563 --> 01:25:53,479
(Ji-min barely mustered up the
courage, but she was eliminated.)

1553
01:25:58,862 --> 01:26:01,814
What about In-seong?
Her heart's breaking, too.

1554
01:26:01,839 --> 01:26:02,839
Oh no.

1555
01:26:02,864 --> 01:26:05,931
(In-seong can't hold back her tears.)

1556
01:26:06,836 --> 01:26:10,720
(No words will comfort her sadness.)

1557
01:26:13,767 --> 01:26:17,440
(Jung-woo spots In-seong crying.)

1558
01:26:19,858 --> 01:26:21,939
- Why are you crying?
- Oh no.

1559
01:26:27,440 --> 01:26:30,560
(They finally became sure
of each other's feelings...)

1560
01:26:30,585 --> 01:26:34,578
Wow, I guess In-seong really liked him.

1561
01:26:35,074 --> 01:26:36,074
Bye.

1562
01:26:36,235 --> 01:26:37,924
Everyone's uncomfortable right now.

1563
01:26:42,729 --> 01:26:47,345
(They suddenly have to say goodbye.)

1564
01:26:53,966 --> 01:26:55,664
Wow, this is crazy.

1565
01:26:57,427 --> 01:26:59,526
(After they leave,)

1566
01:26:59,551 --> 01:27:02,140
(their identities are
revealed to the others.)

1567
01:27:03,907 --> 01:27:06,550
At first, I was in a dilemma.

1568
01:27:06,575 --> 01:27:10,711
$50,000 isn't money you
can just get anywhere.

1569
01:27:11,279 --> 01:27:14,146
But on the other hand,
someone nice that I

1570
01:27:14,171 --> 01:27:17,237
can't meet outside of
this show might show up.

1571
01:27:17,517 --> 01:27:21,024
I can make money later on, but...

1572
01:27:22,411 --> 01:27:25,577
once love passes by,
you can't grab it again.

1573
01:27:26,009 --> 01:27:28,715
I think that timing is important.

1574
01:27:29,480 --> 01:27:30,829
So I pick love over money.

1575
01:27:30,974 --> 01:27:34,411
- I knew it. I knew it.
- She was a Love Catcher.

1576
01:27:34,436 --> 01:27:38,399
I will choose to be a Love Catcher.

1577
01:27:39,083 --> 01:27:42,912
(Yang Ji-min = Love Catcher)

1578
01:27:45,102 --> 01:27:50,373
- Oh no! She mustered up her courage.
- She was innocent.

1579
01:27:51,600 --> 01:27:53,759
They must be so guilty right now.

1580
01:27:56,868 --> 01:28:00,693
I've never really done anything to make
them suspect I was a Money Catcher.

1581
01:28:02,644 --> 01:28:03,777
It's regrettable.

1582
01:28:04,025 --> 01:28:06,175
Did they suspect her
because she was too innocent?

1583
01:28:06,719 --> 01:28:08,957
- But she didn't do anything fishy.
- I know.

1584
01:28:11,311 --> 01:28:16,711
I'm actually 32-year-old Yoon Jung-woo,
the CEO of a start-up consulting company.

1585
01:28:16,736 --> 01:28:18,040
Now it's being revealed.

1586
01:28:18,065 --> 01:28:21,239
(Finally, his real identity is
being revealed to everyone.)

1587
01:28:22,400 --> 01:28:26,139
(The girls found a Money Catcher.)

1588
01:28:26,820 --> 01:28:31,861
Since I run a business, there are times I'm
financially stable and other times I'm not.

1589
01:28:32,938 --> 01:28:36,805
When I'm financially stable,
my relationships go smoothly,

1590
01:28:37,093 --> 01:28:39,045
but when things get tough,

1591
01:28:39,746 --> 01:28:43,939
the one I love tends to leave, and I
get hurt over the most minor words.

1592
01:28:44,618 --> 01:28:49,884
So when I'm doing financially well, I find
it hard to trust people who approach me.

1593
01:28:50,854 --> 01:28:54,290
So since I have the chance
to meet a new person,

1594
01:28:56,097 --> 01:29:00,928
I decided to join, not as a
CEO, but as a freelance travel

1595
01:29:01,389 --> 01:29:05,762
writer, my dream job when I
was younger, to find true love.

1596
01:29:07,014 --> 01:29:10,085
- He met the one though.
- It's too bad. It's too regrettable.

1597
01:29:10,110 --> 01:29:13,485
(He decided to be a Money
Catcher to find true love.)

1598
01:29:14,077 --> 01:29:16,704
In order to find someone
who truly loves me,

1599
01:29:17,190 --> 01:29:18,436
Oh no!

1600
01:29:18,461 --> 01:29:21,833
I will fabricate my job and
join as a Money Catcher.

1601
01:29:23,905 --> 01:29:27,713
(Yoon Jung-woo = Money Catcher)

1602
01:29:28,743 --> 01:29:33,703
If I meet true love, I'll
change my identity then.

1603
01:29:37,045 --> 01:29:39,322
Jung-woo was the one I was interested in.

1604
01:29:41,334 --> 01:29:43,134
So I have a lot on my mind.

1605
01:29:43,926 --> 01:29:47,116
What about In-seong?
What will she do?

1606
01:29:48,970 --> 01:29:52,137
(The moment he thought
he found his true love...)

1607
01:29:53,159 --> 01:29:56,283
(it all ended.)

1608
01:29:56,877 --> 01:30:00,277
(The two people who
came to find true love left...)

1609
01:30:04,263 --> 01:30:05,469
His shoes are gone.

1610
01:30:12,224 --> 01:30:13,780
His things are all gone.

1611
01:30:15,180 --> 01:30:17,108
How come he left right away?

1612
01:30:19,280 --> 01:30:20,685
In-seong, are you okay?

1613
01:30:20,860 --> 01:30:22,764
Yes, I'm okay.

1614
01:30:23,064 --> 01:30:24,289
Oh no.

1615
01:30:24,314 --> 01:30:29,182
If the person I liked was no longer here...

1616
01:30:30,959 --> 01:30:32,092
I'd feel a bit...

1617
01:30:32,627 --> 01:30:34,087
It's kind of complicated.

1618
01:30:34,940 --> 01:30:37,193
They just confirmed their
feelings for each other.

1619
01:30:38,648 --> 01:30:41,745
- Ji-min, too.
- I'm sure it's hard for him, too.

1620
01:30:41,770 --> 01:30:45,097
(Their empty spots feel especially big.)

1621
01:30:46,325 --> 01:30:47,365
My heart breaks.

1622
01:30:47,390 --> 01:30:51,016
Ji-min, who was a Love Catcher,
and Jung-woo, who fabricated

1623
01:30:51,041 --> 01:30:54,250
his job to find true love,
were eventually eliminated.

1624
01:30:54,819 --> 01:31:01,493
- So, Ho-jun got a coin.
- How did this happen?

1625
01:31:02,205 --> 01:31:03,467
Congratulations!

1626
01:31:03,492 --> 01:31:05,167
(Proud)

1627
01:31:05,873 --> 01:31:08,535
The atmosphere is a bit bitter,
but you can't hide your joy.

1628
01:31:08,560 --> 01:31:10,347
Don't think too much about it, you guys.

1629
01:31:11,995 --> 01:31:14,288
- Just go with what you see.
- Got it.

1630
01:31:15,164 --> 01:31:18,164
- He's so cool. I want a coin.
- All righty.

1631
01:31:19,493 --> 01:31:21,287
What's going on? Who are they?

1632
01:31:21,845 --> 01:31:23,384
Excuse me.

1633
01:31:23,753 --> 01:31:26,205
- Hey!
- What's going on?

1634
01:31:26,415 --> 01:31:27,415
That's them?

1635
01:31:29,498 --> 01:31:31,434
Who is the guy you're into?

1636
01:31:31,960 --> 01:31:34,397
Ha-neul has a fixed ideal type.

1637
01:31:34,947 --> 01:31:37,354
She likes guys with a
puppy-type face. Like him.

1638
01:31:52,546 --> 01:31:55,966
I think Ji-min was interested
in you in the beginning.

1639
01:31:56,566 --> 01:31:57,833
That's what I felt.

1640
01:31:59,266 --> 01:32:05,253
I don't think he's just
trying to be friends with you.

1641
01:32:06,044 --> 01:32:09,575
A part of him still likes you.

1642
01:32:13,612 --> 01:32:17,674
(Final Selection D-DAY)

1643
01:32:23,697 --> 01:32:25,297
I'm a bit late, right?

1644
01:32:36,058 --> 01:32:38,156
If you're a Money Catcher,

1645
01:32:38,925 --> 01:32:40,801
take the safe route
and choose me, okay?
